title: chopped beef dip in rye bread
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add sour cream and mayo.
Beat until smooth.
Add beef, onion and garlic powder.
Carve large oval in top of rye bread and scoop out inside, leaving shell about 1/2-inch thick.
Reserve scooped out bread.
Stuff bread shell with dip.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover top and sides with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with crackers and scooped out bread.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Place chops in shallow baking pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place slice of onion on each chop; top with ketchup.
Pour vinegar or pickle juice around chops.
Bake 1 hour or until tender in moderate 350° oven.

title: blend of the bayou seafood casserole
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter using double boiler.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add to the first mixture.
Add soup, mushrooms, seasonings, crab meat and rice.
Mix well.
Place in 2-quart casserole and top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well.
Serves 8.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix well.
Put in refrigerator to set.
May be used in short time.

title: gobs (yankee moon pies)
directions: Cream sugar and crisco.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well on low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Boil raisins and water until boiled down.
Mix oleo, sugar and egg until well blended.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Refrigerate dough a couple of hours.
Make small balls; roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: pone johnnycake corn bread
directions: Bake and sweat!
Eat with bacon and gravy.

title: baked orzo
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in the stick of butter.
Cook the orzo al dente.
Rinse orzo in cold water after cooking; place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle seasoning powder over sauteed onions and peppers; gently stir in all but a few of the onion rings.
Add this mixture to the orzo in the casserole dish; place remaining onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° until hot clear through.
May be frozen before baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: *If possible, use chicken broth in place of water in dressing.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and fold in all ingredients.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked stuffed fish
directions: Crush crackers and add melted oleo and mushrooms.
Spray pan with Pam.
Lay fish and top with stuffing.
Add another layer of fish and finish with stuffing and garlic powder.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cold water and cornstarch to a thin paste.
Combine hot water and sugar in top of a double boiler and bring to a boil over direct heat.
Return to double boiler and add cornstarch paste and cook until mixture begins to thicken.
Cook until thick and smooth, approximately 10 minutes.
Add egg yolks and grated lemon rind and cook a few minutes longer.
Add lemon juice and butter; blend well. Cool, stirring occasionally.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue made from 3 egg whites, 6 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Bake until meringue is set.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg and molasses. Add all dry ingredients. Mix well. Add hot water and beat until smooth. Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan (greased and floured). Bake at 325° for 35 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: artichoke and mushroom casserole
directions: Cook artichoke hearts by directions on box.
Saute mushrooms in butter and drain.
Combine and add soup, sherry and pepper. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Beat butter and margarine until creamy.
Add sugar, flour and rolls oats.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape dough into tiny balls. Place 3 inches apart (on a greased baking sheet).
Flatten with bottom of a glass dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and remove from baking sheet.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Store in tight container.
Sprinkle with additional powdered sugar at serving time.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, stir meat until browned.
Blend in onion soup mix, flour and tomato paste.
Stir in water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Garnish with snipped parsley. Place in the oven topped with bread crumbs and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 325°.
Serve on noodles.

title: zesty salmon loaf
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
Spray a 10-inch nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Set over medium-low heat.
Add pepper and onion. Cook about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally until vegetables are softened.
Using slotted spoon, remove vegetables to bowl.
Let cool slightly.
To bowl add salmon, cereal, oats, eggs, ketchup, lemon juice, mustard and horseradish.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour; brown, stirring constantly. Add water slowly, stirring until thick.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Remove bay leaves and serve over rice.

title: lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water in a small saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice. Cool, then pour into a jar and refrigerate.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice and water slowly until rice absorbs all the water. Add cold milk to rice and simmer.
Add sugar and vanilla (or lemon peel).
Dilute flour in 1/4 cup of water and add to milk mixture, stirring to make sure it doesn't stick.
After it comes to a boil, remove from burner.
Beat eggs and then add to milk mixture (as we do when we make soup).
Mixture should be thick. If not, simmer a little bit more.
Be careful not to curdle eggs.

title: citrusy pecans
directions: Whisk egg white in a medium bowl until frothy. Toss with pecans. Stir together brown sugar and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl. Add pecans and toss. Drain well. Place pecans in a single layer on an aluminum foil-lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Bake at 325°, stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 2 cups.

title: shrimp or seafood sauce
directions: Blend cottage cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and use with shrimp or seafood.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°. Mix eggs, sour cream, water and oil until well blended. Add cake mix and pudding mix and blend well. Stir in entire package of chocolate chips by hand. Pour into a buttered bundt pan. Bake 1 hour. When cool, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done and cut into small pieces.
Add soups, tomatoes and onion.
Spray baking dish with Pam and cover bottom with half of Doritos, crushed.
Pour chicken and soup mixture over this.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Pour one-half of batter into a Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cake batter.
Pour the remaining cake batter and take a knife and cut through batter to make swirls.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and milk.
While cake is still
hot and in the pan, punch holes in cake and pour topping over cake.
Let set 15 to 30 minutes.
Turn cake onto plate.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain canned fruit.
Mix in order given.
Refrigerate 1 hour. Serve.
This makes a wonderfully cool summer treat.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Add
enough
water to cover bottom of crock.
Add onion and bell
pepper.
Salt and pepper beef tips and place on top of veggies.
Add drained mushrooms and pour on gravy.	Do not stir. Cook
on
low
heat
all
day
or high heat for about 4 hours. Serve on rice or creamed potatoes.

title: peanut butter chocolate bonbons
directions: In a large bowl, combine the powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut.
In a small saucepan, melt margarine and peanut butter; pour over coconut mixture.
Blend until mixture is moistened.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in a 375° oven until skins are slightly firm. Remove from oven.
Cool.
Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out potato and save skins.
Mix remaining ingredients with potatoes, using mixer or hand potato masher.
Fill empty skins.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until tops brown.

title: glenda's hot cajun potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together, except potato chips.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish.
Top with the crushed potato chips.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Brown chicken, onion and bell pepper until chicken is just done.
Add tomatoes, lemon juice and seasonings and simmer to desired consistency.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sweet potato sonker
directions: Melt butter in a 10 x 13-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and vanilla (mix well).
Pour into butter.
Put 2 cups of cooked, sliced sweet potatoes all around in top of mixture, but do not stir. In another bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, 1 tsp. vanilla, 1/4 tsp. cinnamon and 2-1/2 cups water.
Mix well.
Pour over top of mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 400 degrees until crust is brown and juice is bubbly.

title: jalapeno chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 heavy sheets of plastic wrap and flatten to 1/4 inch.
Cook chicken in butter in a large skillet over medium heat 5 minutes on each side.
Remove to a serving platter and keep warm.
Add jelly to pan drippings.
Bring to a boil, stirring until smooth.
Spoon over chicken.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Put in jar and store in refrigerator. Keeps indefinitely. To serve, pour on top of cream cheese and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: fluffy lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely.
Split cake horizontally into 2 layers; set aside.

title: golden lemon marmalade
directions: Put carrots, lemon, sugar, salt and water in a large kettle and bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for 10 -15 minutes. Add mint and cook 5 minutes more.
Pour into hot sterilized jelly glasses and seal at once.
Really good stuff not only is this good on muffins or biscuits but makes a great glaze on pork or lamb chops.

title: pasta chicken and fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni, lightly salted; drain and cool under cold water.
Cook chicken breasts the day before so they cube easily. Add chicken to macaroni, then oranges and pineapple.
Cut grapes in half and add.
Moisten with the Marzetti.
If the salad becomes a bit dry (if made the day before), moisten with some of the fruit juices.
This is a tasty salad that you can adjust to your taste. You may not want as much chicken or can add a little more fruit.

title: microwave creamy choco-mint melts
directions: Line bottom and sides of 12 x 8-inch pan (glass is best) with waxed paper.
Combine 2/3 of the almond bark with the morsels.
Put in 4-cup glass measure.
Microwave on High, uncovered, about 2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Spread 1/2 of this on bottom of pan. Refrigerate just until set, then remove from refrigerator.
Place remaining bark in 2-cup glass measure.
Microwave on High about 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir until smooth.
Add a drop or two of food coloring and peppermint.
Add a little milk only if green mixture gets stiff.
Spread over chocolate layer.
Refrigerate and remove as before.
Microwave remaining chocolate about 30 seconds.
Spread over mint layer.
Allow to set at room temperature, then cut into small pieces.
These are especially pretty on a Christmas plate.

title: four layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix oleo, flour and 1/2 cup nuts; pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: blend of the bayou seafood
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter in double boiler. Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter. Mix all together and put in 3-quart casserole dish. Top with grated cheese and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly. Allow to stand for a while before serving. Freezes well before baking. Serves 8.

title: basic vanilla pudding
directions: Bring 1 1/2 cups milk to boil in saucepan.
While milk warms, mix remaining ingredients in 1/2 cup milk, using 2 tablespoons to 3/4 cup sugar, depending on desired sweetness.
Add well mixed ingredients into saucepan when milk boils.
Stir until thickened. Serve warm or chilled.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Cook hamburger (mixture shaped into balls) in tomato sauce and water.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
If desired, 1 cup nuts may be added.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cool cooked and drained eggplant.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to eggplant.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, cumin and salt.
Drain well. In a large Dutch oven, combine beef chili powder, flour and sugar. Add tomato paste, kidney beans and tomatoes; stir well.
Cover and simmer at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy.
Add sugar and lemon.
Add sour cream, then blend La Creme in on low speed (not too much).
Place a small bowl in the middle of a large plate.
Place fresh strawberries around bowl.

title: play clay
directions: Mix salt and cornstarch in cooking pot.
Slowly stir in water, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Cook and stir over low heat until it is stiff, like mashed potatoes. This will take 2 to 3 minutes.
Spoon the mixture into an old pie tin or piece of aluminum foil.
Let cool for about 10 minutes.
When mixture is cool enough to handle, press and squeeze it until it feels like clay, about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water; stir until well blended. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining butter.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chunks.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients; chill until ready to serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place half of lettuce in deep salad bowl.
Top with celery, green pepper, onion and peas, in that order.
Cover with rest of lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise on top and sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed in large rectangle pan.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Add 12 ounce Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple and spread over cake.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over coconut and dot with cherries.
Don't skimp on the Cool Whip.
The thicker the icing the better the taste.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix margarine, egg and cake mix.
Press into 11 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and nuts.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool thoroughly and cut into squares.

title: cabbage stew
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Add shredded cabbage, 1/2 cup of water and tomatoes.
Cook for 15 minutes, then add chili powder, beans, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Combine all ingredients in large cooker and simmer for 2 hours.

title: sourdough starter(basic batter)
directions: In glass or crock bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Add flour and remaining water.
Mix well and allow to stand, loosely covered, in warm place 3 to 5 days.
Each time batter is used, reserve 1 cup batter to use as a starter for another batch.
May be kept in refrigerator indefinitely.

title: carrot cake
directions: Measure and sift together sugar, flour soda, cinnamon and salt.
Sift into oil and stir.
Add 4 whole eggs and stir well, add carrots and nuts and stir well.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2 pan at 300 for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: salt rising bread
directions: Place in hot water (stir occasionally) until yeast begins to rise, about 4 to 5 hours.
Make stiff dough, adding salt and shortening.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Grease loaf with melted shortening.
Raise over hot water.
Bake in moderate oven, beginning slowly.

title: spam meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with undiluted chicken soup. Place in 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: my favorite cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour into a spring-form pan or pie plate (don't grease).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool cheesecake and serve plain or with Cool Whip topping.

title: heavenly cheesecake
directions: Line sides and bottom of spring-form pan with ladyfingers. Blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy. In another bowl, whip the cream until "whipped cream" consistency. (Chill bowl and beaters to help cream "set.")
Combine the 2 bowls and blend.
Pour into pan halfway up. Add layer of ladyfingers. Pour remaining mixture on top. Add strawberries (optional). Refrigerate.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place butter in a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Melt in microwave on High.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk. Cook on High for 10 minutes, stirring at 4-3-3 minute intervals. Add potatoes and cook on High for 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Stir in Velveeta cheese cubes and melt on High for 3 minutes.
Stir gently.
Serves 6.

title: good old fashion dressing
directions: Blend first 7 ingredients
in blender until quite fine. Pour bouillon cubes in water over the bread: add to the first ingredients and stuff bird. Double this for large bird.

title: basic layer recipe for your layer cake
directions: Cream
butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time. Alternate milk and flour.
Add vanilla.
Stir in baking powder last.
Grease and lightly flour 9-inch layer cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef in a little oil in a large deep frying pan until brown, stirring often.
Drain fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni shells.
Drain; rinse.
Pour half the shells into deep casserole.
Cover with half of the meat sauce.
Spread half the sour cream over sauce.
Top with slices of Provolone.
Repeat, ending with slices of Mozzarella.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking until cheese browns slightly.

title: baked orange roughy
directions: In a microwave-safe baking dish, melt just enough butter or margarine to cover the bottom of the dish you are using. Sprinkle finely chopped onions over melted butter or margarine. Lay fillets upside down in dish and sprinkle with salt and ground pepper to taste.

Then cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Remove from oven and carefully turn fish over with a spatula, then pour the white wine and lemon juice over top. Sprinkle with seasoned bread crumbs and parsley flakes.
Cover again with plastic wrap and microwave on High for another 5 minutes.
Remove plastic wrap and enjoy!!!

title: oven baked "mock" kentucky fried chicken
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in a plastic bag.
Spray broiler pan and rack with Pam.
Wash chicken and let drain.
Dredge in flour mixture and place on broiler pan.
Drizzle chicken with melted butter or spray chicken with Pam (to save calories and fat grams).
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Extra flour mixture may be frozen for next time.

title: lemon cake
directions: Finely grate the rinds of both lemons.

title: hungarian-chicken paprika ex!
directions: Saute onion in cooking oil in Dutch oven.
Add approximately 3 tablespoons paprika and stir well.
Add chicken pieces, one by one, and coat each with thyme, onion and paprika.
Add salt and carrot rounds.
Cover and cook slowly, approximately 3/4 hour, turning chicken occasionally (there should be enough juice but you may have to add a bit of water).
Taste.
You may need more salt.
Cook noodles.
Add green pepper and continue approximately 15 minutes. Remove chicken pieces to bed of cooked noodles.
Stir sour cream into broth and pour over chicken.
Serve with salad.

title: chicken avocado salad for 3
directions: Cook chicken breasts covered with water.
Add salt and bay leaf.
Bone, skin and cube chicken breasts.
Mash eggs; chop celery and green onions.
Combine; add mayonnaise to consistency you want.
Serve on half avocados.	Garnish any way you want.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Place ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Drizzle melted butter over all and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: smokey link casserole
directions: Spray a large dish and layer the following. Place diced smokey links in the bottom of dish, then place cooked and drained veggies over meat. Follow this by cooked noodles.
Mix soup and milk together; pour over noodles. Top with mushroom pieces if desired. Add diced Velveeta cheese and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients all together.
First put margarine in a pan; let melt.
Put 2 tablespoons flour, mushroom juice and 1/2 cup milk in; stir all up and cook until thick.
Pour over noodles. Bake.
Equals bread substitute, limited vegetable and fat - 1/2 milk.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1/2 beef and rest of ingredients.
Roll in two or three balls.
Roll balls in remaining beef.

title: delicious fruitcake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and mix with nuts and coconut.
Pour condensed milk over all and blend.
Add vanilla and dash of salt.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Soften butter.
Beat in sugar, egg, soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Add nuts.
Mix by hand.
Divide in two parts.
Roll in wax paper and freeze.
Cut thin slices and bake 10 minutes at 350°. Remove from pan right away.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Bake potatoes and take out of skins.
Do not mash, leave in small chunks.
Place in 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Heat 1/4 cup butter and soup.
Add sour cream, onion and cheese to soup mixture and stir.
Pour over potatoes and top with corn flakes crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cut up 1 cup strawberries; add to the 1 cup cold water and the 3 tablespoons cornstarch that have been stirred until smooth. Place in a saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring until thick and clear.
Stir in a few drops of red food coloring.
Cool. Stir in remaining berries, reserving 1/4 cup for garnishing.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Chill for about 3 hours until firm.
Top with whipping cream and garnish.

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: In saucepan, bring dates, water, 1/2 cup sugar and nuts to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Cream shortening and rest of sugars. Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick and spread with date mixture.
Roll in wax paper and chill overnight. Bake at 400°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly and chill.

title: pineapple salsa
directions: Combine all and refrigerate overnight.
If too sweet, add more lime juice.
If not sweet enough, add more sugar.

title: party potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slightly thaw potatoes.
Combine with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Add seasonings, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese; blend thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased 3-quart casserole.
Combine corn flakes with remaining butter; sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Yields fourteen 1/2-cup servings.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in the boiling water.
Add the strawberries to the jello as soon as jello is dissolved.
Add the crushed pineapple.
Put half of jello in pan to make 1 layer; let set a while.
Have cheese softened; add pineapple juice and chopped nuts. Spread cheese over layer of jello; add balance of jello.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 11 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown for 45 minutes.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate squares over low heat in a large saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and slightly beaten eggs. Mix thoroughly.
Add flour and baking powder.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into 9 X 13 pan, greased and floured on bottom only.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Form into ball. Roll in pecans.
Let set overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.

title: scripture cake(a puzzle just for you)
directions: Follow directions of Solomon for bringing up a child.
Proverbs 23:14.
That is, beat him with a rod.
Bake as a loaf cake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Cool on a rack.
Slices best after a few hours. All references are KJV.

title: swiss shrimp fantasies
directions: In medium bowl, combine shrimp and all other ingredients, except bread. (This mix can be covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours in advance). Preheat oven to 450. Top each slice of bread with about 1 Tbsp. of the mixture. Arrange a single layer on a greased baking sheet. Bake until the top is golden brown and bubbly (8-10 minutes, depends on the oven). Serve immediately!

title: cream puffs
directions: Add shortening and salt to boiling water and stir over medium heat until mixture boils. Lower heat; add flour all at once and stir vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan. Remove from heat and add 1 egg at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Shape on an ungreased cookie sheet using 1 teaspoon or 1 tablespoon of paste for 1 puff, depending on size desired. Bake in hot oven, 450°, for 20 minutes. Do not open the door. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake about 20 minutes more. Remove and place on rack to cool. When cold, make slit on one side of each puff with sharp knife. Fill with whipped cream. Dust tops with powdered sugar.

title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Combine sugar and flour and coat beef (I use brown bag and shake a few pieces at a time).
Brown beef in large stock pot in melted shortening (or oil).
Add seasonings, tomatoes and broth to meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat about 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Stir in vegetables, except peas; cover and cook about 30 minutes.
Add peas; cover and cook about 15 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp louisiana
directions: Cook onions in butter until soft.
Add shrimp, which has been cleaned and broken into pieces.
Cook until brown.
Stir in flour, salt and chili powder.
Gradually add the milk.
Cook 5 minutes. Add catsup and parsley.
Steam about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt in a saucepan the butter and brown sugar until dissolved. Cool ingredients slightly.
Beat in well the eggs and vanilla. Sift, then measure 1 cup flour; resift it with baking powder and salt.
Stir flour mixture into butter mixture and add the chocolate bits or nuts, or combination of both.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: cheese bars
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Line with whole graham crackers.

title: mike's potato soup
directions: Cook bacon in a soup pan.
When crisp, remove bacon.
Drain and set aside.

title: german nut cookies
directions: Cream the cheese and oleo and mix well.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Punch holes in baked brownies.
Pour Kahlua or coffee mixture over brownies.
Let soak while you mix mousse.
Layer in bowl in following order:
1/2 brownie, 1/2 mousse, 1/2 candy and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers and let set at least 24 hours.

title: meat ball stew
directions: Mix beef with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, egg, minced onion and bread crumbs.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Brown in hot oil.
Remove balls from skillet; pour off all fat except 3 tablespoons.
(If you have less than 3 tablespoons, add more oil.) Blend in flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; simmer over low heat 10 minutes, adding more water if necessary. Add to meat balls in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until veggies are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked onions
directions: Butter 2-quart shallow baking dish. Melt stick of butter in skillet over medium heat and add onions. Cook 10 to 12 minutes until tender. Pour into casserole. Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper in bowl and pour over onions. Sprinkle with cheese. Melt extra butter; dip one side of bread in it. Arrange on top (butter side up) to completely cover top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown. Serves 8.

title: creole casserole
directions: Place half of beef in bottom of shallow, greased casserole. Cover with half of carrots, celery, onions and green pepper slices.
Sprinkle with half the seasonings.
Repeat the next layer, beginning with the ground beef; top with mushrooms.
Mix tomato soup and mushroom juice; pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: glazed popcorn balls
directions: Place popcorn in a large bowl.
Heat butter and syrup in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir in sugar and gelatin. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and stir gently for 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn, tossing until everything is coated. Make into balls. Can make small or large balls.

title: green rice
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over package of frozen broccoli. Stir occasionally until thawed.
Saute margarine, celery and onion.
Mix together rice, soup, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and water, celery and onion.
Bake in casserole dish for 40 minutes at 325°.

title: strawberry pretzel delite
directions: Mix together and line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with this mixture.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: turtle squares
directions: Mix together and spread 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13 pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Melt 30 caramel squares in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Drizzle over baked batter.
Sprinkle 1 cup pecan pieces and 1 cup chocolate chips on top.
Drop the remaining batter in blotches over nuts and chips.
Bake 20-25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: 3 layer gelatin
directions: Mix and cool.
Pour in 9-inch square pan sprayed with Pam. Chill until firm.

title: chicken and artichokes
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown 12 to 15 minutes in 4 tablespoons margarine.
Remove chicken and put into a casserole dish.
Add remaining margarine to pan and saute mushrooms about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, bouillon and sherry. Cook and stir about 5 minutes.
Arrange artichoke hearts over chicken.
Pour sauce on top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: southern fried cabbage
directions: Heat bacon fat in a skillet; toss in cabbage and stir until it's glistening.
Lower the heat; add in pepper flakes and season with salt to taste.
Continue cooking and turning cabbage until it is barely tender, about 10 minutes.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover; blend for 20 seconds.
Chill before serving.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Mix well mashed potatoes, yeast, warm water, salt and sugar. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Add well beaten eggs and shortening to first mixture and beat well.
Add flour enough to handle easily. Knead.
Let rise double in bulk.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out doughnuts.
Let rise double again.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain on rack or paper towels.
Sugar or glaze while still warm.

title: rigatoni with broccoli
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken, garlic and pepper. Saute 4 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned.
In small bowl, stir broth, cornstarch and salt; add to skillet.
Stir in broccoli.
Bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute. Reduce heat to low; cook 4 minutes longer or until heated through. Toss with rigatoni.
Makes 8 servings.

title: parmesan garlic chicken
directions: Mix cheese, garlic powder and salad dressing mix. Moisten chicken with water; coat with cheese mixture. Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes; cut in strips about 1 inch thick.
Place in a 3 quart baking dish.
Mix sugar and flour well.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Top with butter or oleo.
Cover casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir once about halfway through baking.

title: special pumpkin bread(the best pumpkin bread)
directions: Mix oil, water, eggs and sugar; stir in pumpkin.
Mix all dry ingredients together first, then stir in the liquid ingredients. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 greased loaf pans; sprinkle topping before baking.
Top with topping.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crush Oreos.
Line 9-inch pie pan or an 8-inch square pan with most of crushed cookies (save some for topping).
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Cream again.
Add almond flavoring.
Spread this mixture on crumbs.
Whip cream with sugar.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Fold until well blended.
Spread this on first mixture.
Cover with crushed wafers.
Let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: glorified rice
directions: Stir together; top each serving with a maraschino cherry.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables and celery 10 minutes; drain.
Add onions and water chestnuts.
Blend mayonnaise and soup.
Fold in mixed vegetables to which 1/2 of grated cheese has been added. Sprinkle 1/2 cup Pepperidge Farm dressing on bottom of a slightly greased casserole dish.
Add vegetable mixture.
Top with dressing and cheese which have been mixed with melted butter.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix pudding (as directed on box.)
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Place 2nd layer crackers over mix.
Place rest of mixture over crackers.
Place 3rd layer of crackers over mix. Cover and refrigerate.

title: birdseed salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add onion. Add raisins, sunflower seeds, bacon bits, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Stir all together and mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together all ingredients, except Doritos and cheese.
Layer in long casserole: chicken mixture, Doritos and cheese.
Repeat layers ending with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: shoyu chicken
directions: Pound the meat flat.
Marinate for up to 4 hours for 5 pounds of chicken.
Grill.

title: oatmeal sandwich cookies
directions: In mixing bowl cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Beat in vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoon
2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 - 12 minutes or until brown.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and zucchini.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture; beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Batter will be runny.

title: giant soap bubbles
directions: Mix water and detergent and add 2 tablespoons of glycerine. Take a coat hanger and bend it into a loop.
Dip hanger into solution and wave it in the air.

title: for goodness sakes salad
directions: In a large bowl dissolve the gelatines in hot water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in the milk, pineapple with juice, mayo, cottage cheese, nuts and horseradish sauce.
Mix well.
Chill until partially set.
Pour into an oiled 8 ounce mold.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, raisins and spices.
Mix well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots.
Layer carrots, green pepper and onions in a large serving dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over carrots.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.
Serves 16.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: dutch apple rice pudding
directions: In medium bowl, combine rice, applesauce, 1/2 of sugar, 2 tablespoons
of butter, raisins and vanilla; set aside.
In another
bowl, combine cracker crumbs and coconut with remaining sugar
and 4 tablespoons butter; mix well.
In a buttered 2-quart casserole,
sprinkle
cup
of the crumb mixture. Pour
in all
of
the
rice
mixture; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes or until top
is
golden. Serve
warm
with apple slices or ice cream. Makes 8 servings.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Put meat into a deep saucepot or Dutch oven.
Add soup mix, peppercorns, garlic, bay leaf and water.
Cover; bring to boiling and simmer 3 1/2 hours.
Add vegetables, placing cabbage on top of meat.
Cover and cook 1 hour, or until tender.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Puree berries in blender for 1/2 minute.
Measure 1 quart of berries in a large saucepan.
Add spices, lemon juice and Sure-Jell.
Place over high heat and bring to hard boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add sugar all at once.
Again, bring to hard rolling boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly. Skim off foam and pour into jars and seal.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch well-greased loaf pan, the bottom lined with wax paper.
Bake about 40 minutes at 325° or an hour at 300°.
Good luck!

title: cream cheese danish
directions: In 9 x 13-inch greased pan, roll out 1 package of rolls.
Lay in bottom of pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg yolk until fluffy.
Spread mixture over rolls in bottom of pan. Roll out other package of rolls and lay on top of mixture.
Brush with egg yolk.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° until golden brown. Let cool completely before cutting.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream together the butter, brown sugar and almond extract. Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder; blend into butter mixture.
Place on cookie sheet; pat into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick, using as little flour as possible.
Make cut marks to prick each square with tines of fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until light and golden.
Do not overcook.
Remove squares; cool and store in tin with tight lid.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese reach room temperature.
Whip cheeses together until smooth (can use electric mixer).
Add other ingredients and blend well.
Put mixture in refrigerator for about 2 hours before shaping into ball.
Roll ball or 2 rolls in chopped pecans.

title: lima bean scallop
directions: Place lima beans in a saucepan and cover with water.
Soak overnight.
Add onion and bring to boil.
Cook over low heat until tender and drain.
Add soup, 1/2 cup water and butter and pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Add sweet cream and flour alternately.
Bake at 300° in tube pan for about 1 3/4 hours. While cake is baking, prepare glaze.

title: meat loaf manhattan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop onion and garlic to desired size and mix with all ingredients, except oats and barbecue sauce, with your hands.
It is helpful if you let the meat rest from the refrigerator before you start.
Add 1/2 sauce and oats and continue to mix well.
Form your loaf and put the remaining sauce on top and sides.
Bake about 40 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except jalapenos and shredded cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 jalapenos and cheese.
Add remaining mixture and top with cheese and jalapenos.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 square pans, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch or 3 round pans 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Line bottom of pans with waxed paper.
Pour boiling water on chocolate, stirring until chocolate is melted; cool.

title: chicken breast divan
directions: Pound chicken between waxed paper.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Melt butter, mix with olive oil in micro safe dish.
Add chicken.
Coat both sides.
Microwave 3 minutes on High.
Reset 1 minute.
Turn chicken and microwave 3 more minutes on High or until chicken is tender.
Mix chives, onions, lemon juice, mustard and parsley.
Microwave 1 minute on High.
Add juice from chicken and broth.
Stir until smooth and pour over chicken.
Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: devil's food float
directions: Pour the heated sauce on top of the cake mixture in the pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
During baking the sauce goes to the bottom and the cake "floats" to the top.
Serve with or without whipped cream.

title: horns
directions: Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Then add flour, small amount at a time.
When well mixed, add nuts.
Shape into small horns.
Take rounded teaspoonful or more, if you like, and roll between your palms into elongated, rounded strip, as thick as you like.
Then turn up the ends into horn shape.
Bake for 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
When still warm, roll in powdered sugar until well coated.
It's easy and they're delicious.

title: banana bread
directions: Put eggs, oil, milk and bananas in blender or food processor. Mix well on low speed.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to blender.
Mix on low speed until moistened.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine until clear.

Add broccoli and stock and cook until tender. Add and blend half and half cream. Add grated or cut up cheese. Cook until cheese is all melted and soup is thickening. Dissolve cornstarch in 1 cup water. Add if thicker soup is desired.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crush Pecan Sandies. Mix the Sandies with melted margarine. Press into a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown. Using a mixer, blend cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust. Mix lemon pudding and milk. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Spread rest of Cool Whip over lemon mixture. Crush the remaining Pecan Sandies that you reserved and sprinkle on top of the spread Cool Whip.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Note:
Makes enough mix for many jars.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients in a pan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes doughy in consistency. Knead until cool.
Model different colors of clay into any shape you can imagine.
Not edible.
Can be used over and over again. Keeps 3 months unrefrigerated.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and 1/2 of the cake mix until smooth.
Then stir in remaining cake mix until smooth.
Roll dough out and cut into any desired shape or square.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Poke fork holes in when fresh out of oven.
Put ice cream between two cookies and freeze.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a greased 2 1/2 quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together and beat well.
Makes 3 layers.
Cook at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: antipasta
directions: Drain first 4 ingredients.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Bring marinade to a boil and pour over mixture.
Refrigerate 8 hours.

title: southern hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients first.
Add onion, buttermilk and well beaten egg in order.
Mix well.
Drop spoonful into hot oil and cook until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Grate cucumber and then drain it.
Add the remaining ingredients. You may use a blender if desired.
Serve with chips, vegetables, etc.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef together.
Pour into a crock-pot.
Cut Velveeta into cubes and also put into crock-pot. Drain chili peppers and tomatoes; add these and remaining ingredients to the meat and cheese.
Heat on medium heat for 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour salad dressing on top. Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain off excess liquid. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple juice and save. Place pineapple in 9 inch dish. Mix flour and sugar with 3 tablespoons of juice and pour over the pineapple. Sprinkle cheese over pineapple. Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs; crumble over top for crust. Bake at 300° for 30-45 minutes or until brown.

title: deep, dark chocolate cake(mixes in 5 minutes)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into floured and greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes clean.
Cool.
Frost with One-Bowl Buttercream Frosting.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add oleo, pumpkin, egg and water.
Mix until moist.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour and 10 minutes (70 minutes) or until done.

title: creamed onions
directions: Slice onions into rings.
Combine water, vinegar and sugar and bring to a boil.

title: brownies
directions: Melt oleo; mix in sugar, eggs and cocoa.
Add flour and nuts. Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: italian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with Italian seasoning and brown in skillet. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and chicken soup. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with Cheddar cheese; bake 15 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes. Slice lengthwise and scoop out all the pulp. Mix the pulp with cheese, mayonnaise, milk and egg; beat until smooth. Fill potato skins with mixture and top with chopped green onions, bacon bits and additional shredded cheese. Bake until hot and cheese melts.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Cook as you would any cream pie filling.
Cool.
This is a good filling for any kind of pie, banana, coconut, etc.

title: double-nutted banana bread
directions: Mix flour, soda
and
salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter and	sugar.	Add
eggs,
beating after each addition; add vanilla
and
mashed
bananas.
Beat.
Add water and nuts.	Mix. Pour
into	greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven
for
hour and 10 minutes.	Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Remove and cool completely.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Fry tortillas, one at a time, in hot shortening a few seconds. Drain. Fill each tortilla with the onion and grated cheese; roll. Place in shallow baking dish. Cover with enchilada sauce and top with grated cheese.
Heat at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil
sweet
potatoes in skins until fork tender.
Peel and mash
with
butter until smooth and creamy.
Mix in sugar and milk;
add egg and beat briskly with fork to blend.
Stir in vanilla, nutmeg, lemon juice and salt; pour into pie shell. Bake in
hot
oven (400°) for 30 to 35 minutes until pastry is nicely browned
and
filling
seems
set
around edges.
Cool before cutting.
Very Southern!

title: strawberry shakes
directions: You will need measuring cup, blender, ice cream scoop, 3 tall glasses and straws.

title: hot spice o.j.
directions: Mix sugars, cinnamon and cloves with cider or juice.
Heat to below simmering; add to orange juice.
Serve in mugs and garnish with fruit slices.

title: crab imperial
directions: Place crab meat in baking pan or dish.
(Do not stir crab meat.
Keep in lumps as much as possible.)
Saute peppers in half of the butter.
Mix other ingredients together except for the remainder of the butter and bread crumbs.
Stir into crab meat. Melt butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Spread bread crumbs on top of crab meat.
Bake at 350° until top is browned.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 2 or 3 teaspoons to each cup boiling water.

title: country meat loaf
directions: Combine bread and milk in large mixing bowl.
Combine beef, sausage, onions, celery and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine rest of ingredients; mix well and pack into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Pour off any extra fat before removing the loaf to a warm platter.

title: frozen salad(very good)
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese well.
Add drained pineapple, strawberries (juice, too) and Cool Whip.
Fold in sliced bananas and nuts.
Add a little red food coloring to make a "pretty pink." Freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs, oil and water as directed on box.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed. Blend well after each addition to coat with batter.
This will be very thick.
May save a few cherry halves and walnuts to decorate cake.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 300° until cake tests done.
Cool.

title: toffee butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add sugar, syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring now and then, to 300°.
Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts.
Spread in well-greased 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend ingredients 2 through 7 in a bowl, then add cream cheese and blend well.
Leave in bowl or design your own or mold and garnish with shrimp and cocktail sauce, including celery.
Good with crackers and celery sticks.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti with onion; drain.
Add tomatoes and sauteed mushrooms.
Combine with diced chicken.
Mix in half the grated cheese.
Add seasonings and cream.
Put in casserole and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand (do not use mixer).
Fold in 1 large tub of Cool Whip.
This recipe is delicious and quick. Refrigerate.
Miniature marshmallows can be added if you like. Will keep 2 weeks or more in the refrigerator.

title: good fruit salad
directions: Chop or slice first 4 ingredients.
Add raisins and walnuts. Toss and add Russian dressing.
Let set overnight.

title: cold cantaloupe soup
directions: Peel and chop cantaloupe coarsely.
Puree with remaining ingredients in food processor.
Chill until serving time.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Serves 4.

title: crumb pudding
directions: Mix everything up real well.
Grease deep cake pan, cook at about 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until it is golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked salmon with vegetables and herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Fill large pot with water to depth of 1 inch.
Place steamer rack in pot and bring to boil.
Place potatoes and carrots on steamer rack.
Cover pot and steam for 5 minutes. Add green beans and steam 5 more minutes.
Transfer vegetables to bowl.
Add olive oil, soy sauce, leeks, green onions, dill and basil; toss well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place 4 large foil sheets on baking sheet.
Spray foil with vegetable oil spray. Place 1 salmon fillet on each foil sheet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon vegetable mixture evenly over salmon.
Top each with 1 tablespoon butter.
Wrap foil around salmon and vegetable and seal.
Bake until fish is opaque, about 14 minutes.
Transfer salmon to plates and discard foil.
Serves 4.

title: jeff's deer jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients, except venison (deer meat) together and stir well. Place venison into mixture and let marinate for at least 6 hours. Place in dehydrator about 8 hours.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Prepare Kraft dinner as on box, but use 3/4 cup milk instead. Saute onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Mix all together; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix both sugars, spice and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg white and water in another bowl until mixture is frothy.
Add pecan halves to egg white mixture and stir until pecans are coated.
Pour into sugar-spice mixture and stir until coated. Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake at 250° until dry.
Stir every ten minutes.

title: kendra's rainbow cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugars, vanilla, egg and slowly add flour. When well mixed, drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Place Rainbow morsels on top of cookies. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a large bowl, place ingredients in layers.

title: vanilla cookies(club member: terah)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla. Beat well. Shape into roll and wrap in foil. Chill until firm. Slice 1/4 inch thick and bake at 400° on ungreased baking sheet about 10 minutes.
Remove cookies to cooling rack.

title: lemony corn-on-the-cob, grilled
directions: Remove husks and silk from corn just before grilling.
Combine butter and lemon-pepper seasoning.
Spread on corn and place each ear on piece of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Roll foil lengthwise around each ear and twist foil at each end.
Grill corn, covered, over medium hot coals 20 minutes, turning after 10 minutes.

title: texas millionaire candy
directions: Melt
caramels
with milk in double boiler.
Add pecans. Drop by
teaspoon
onto greased wax paper.
Grease fingers and press pieces
into shape.
Melt chocolate and paraffin and dip candy.

title: muffin yeast bread
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Blend in other ingredients; beat for 1 minute.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Fill each muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: layered peach cobbler
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer ingredients in the order they are listed. Do NOT stir. Peaches are listed twice in the ingredients because there are two layers of peaches. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: deep dish apple crisp
directions: Slice apples and toss with lemon juice.
Mix next 4 ingredients with apples.
Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix last 3 ingredients together until crumbly; spread over apples. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening until it looks like small peas in the flour.
Add only enough water to make a soft dough.
Mix well, then knead on a well-floured board for 5 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 30 minutes to rest.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Soak sliced zucchini overnight (do not peel). Grind bell pepper, pimientos, tomatoes, celery and hot peppers coarsely.
Add canning salt and stir well. Cover and let set overnight.
Drain and rinse well in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Cook for 45 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pack in hot jars and seal.
If needed, add water (about 1 cup).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage and drain.
Beat eggs with mustard and milk (use some salt if desired).
Layer bread, then sausage, then cheese in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

title: sesame-glazed parsnips
directions: Boil parsnips and carrots together until just tender.
Toast sesame seed in skillet over medium heat.
When they begin to turn color, add butter, maple syrup, salt and orange juice.
Stir in carrots and parsnips.
Turn heat to medium-high and cook, stirring until liquid is reduced to a glaze.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift together flour,
meal,
baking
powder,
sugar and salt. Beat eggs slightly and
add milk.
Stir in dry ingredients; add shortening.
Dip
wieners
into batter, holding with fork or skewer, drain excess
batter
back	into bowl.
Fry in wire basket in oil heated to 375° until golden brown; drain on absorbent paper.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Line dish with dried beef.
Wrap 1 strip of bacon around each breast.
Place on top of beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together and spoon on top of chicken.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked ham, potatoes and onions
directions: Place the slice of ham in the roasting pan.
Peel and slice the potatoes; spread them over the ham.
Sift flour and paprika over the potatoes.
Peel and slice the onions on top of the flour mixture.
Half cover the ingredients with milk.
Cover the dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Uncover for the last 10 minutes of cooking time.

title: sausage biscuit bites
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet until browned, stirring to crumble. Drain well and set aside.
Combine the next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add yeast mixture to buttermilk, stirring well.
Add buttermilk mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until the dry ingredients are moistened.
Knead in sausage.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly 3 to 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 1 3/4-inch round cutter.
Place biscuit on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 3 dozen biscuits.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges together.
Have ready jello, dissolved according to directions.
Add fruit mixture. When slightly set add sugar.
Mix in a little red food coloring. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Makes a large amount.

title: debi's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just thawed; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except crackers and stir.
Top with finely chopped, toasted crackers, enough to completely cover top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 2 to 2 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.

title: pumpkin orange cake roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line a 15x10inch jellyroll pan with foil. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Prepare cake as directed adding 1 1/2 teaspoon orange peel at end. Bake for 30 minutes. Sprinkle a towel with powdered sugar; turn cake onto towel, peel off foil. Roll up cake and towel; cool. Combine pumpkin, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and orange peel in a bowl. Unroll cake; spread over cake. Reroll cake. Sprinkle with sugar. Spoon jelly into small bag. Cut off corner squeeze to drizzle over cake. Chill.

title: sausage gravy
directions: Brown sausage meat; pour off most of grease.
Add flour to absorb remainder of grease.
Pour in milk; add salt and pepper. Simmer.
Water may be added if gravy becomes too thick.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(used often, because it's easy)
directions: Beat 1 minute in blender sugar, Bisquick, butter or oleo, evaporated milk, eggs, pumpkin and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
Serve with whipped topping.
Good for 9 to 10-inch pie plate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix and put in Pyrex dish.
Cover with one can tomato sauce. Cook 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: grand champion sponge cake
directions: Sift together the flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar, a little at a time; beat until whites form stiff, but not dry, peaks.
In a medium bowl, combine yolks, water, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients. Beat at medium high speed for 4 minutes, or until mixture is light and fluffy.
Fold yolk mixture gently, but thoroughly, into the beaten egg whites.
Turn into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Invert pan to cool.

title: crisco rum flavored cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Stir in flavoring.
Grease and flour pan lightly and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Do not open oven door or shake floor before time is up.
Tested and tried recipe.

title: moc lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Brown ground beef.
Add Sloppy Joes mix and tomatoes; simmer.
Layer noodles, meat and a dollop of cream cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Cover with foil if you like juicy lasagna.
Serve with Parmesan cheese, salad and bread.

title: versie's strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and food coloring.
Cook until clear and thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Cool until almost begins to thicken.
Put fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries when mixture is cooled.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with fresh strawberries.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Stew squash and onions until tender enough to mash. Add salt and pepper. In 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of squash, cracker crumbs and soup. Bake at 400° until top browns. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add strawberries (can be added while frozen) and mix.
Add remaining fruit.
Pour half into 2-quart mold and let gel.
(Leave other half out so it won't set.) Add sour cream and let stand firm.
Add remaining jello mixture and let stand until firm.
Can be made the day before.
Serves 8.

title: raisin cake
directions: Put raisins in bowl with water and let stand for 10 minutes. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with raisin mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Crumble half of the baked cake into punch bowl.
Mix instant pudding according to package directions.
Pour half over the cake in bowl. Spoon half the pineapple, pie filling, Cool Whip and coconut into bowl. Crumble remaining cake in bowl and repeat the layers of ingredients.

title: lazy day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
In greased baking dish, make layers of noodles, cottage cheese, cheese slices and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat sequence.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: festive mix
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In large bowl combine all ingredients except bacon bits.
Evenly spread half of mixture on a well-greased 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Stir half of the bacon bits into the mixture evenly.
Continue baking another 10 minutes or until light golden brown.
Turn onto waxed paper.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Cool.
Make second pan with remaining ingredients.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Layer 10 x 13-inch dish with graham crackers, pudding mixture, graham crackers and pudding mixture, ending with graham crackers and top with chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in large mixer bowl and blend well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken to tender.
Let cool, then bone and cut into pieces.
Saute onion in margarine; add broccoli.
Place all ingredients in slightly greased casserole in this order: dry rice, chicken, onions and broccoli, soups and liquid.
Stir and then sprinkle with almonds or crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Can be made ahead of time and kept in refrigerator until cooking time.

title: molded vegetable relish
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar and onion.
Chill until thickened slightly.
Fold in vegetables.
Pour into 3 or 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold; garnish, if desired.
Yields 5 servings.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Blend oleo, egg, sugar, biscuit mix and flavoring. When smooth, mix in potato flakes. With a spoon, place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Roll ball size of thumb. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Add 1 cube margarine. Boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows (10 miniature marshmallows equal 1 regular size).
Stir until melted. Add pecans (optional), coconut, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir it in thoroughly.
Add oil slowly, beating constantly, and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat for a few minutes.
Store in a cool place or refrigerate, but do not freeze.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichoke hearts through your fingers into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Transfer into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until brown and bubbly.
Serves well with Triscuits.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Dip your favorite vegetable and enjoy.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat one minute at medium speed of electric mixer.
Combine next 5 ingredients; add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat one minute at medium speed.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Combine garlic, butter, tarragon and marjoram; cream until well blended.
Add bread crumbs and lemon juice, mix well. Alternate layers of shrimp and bread crumbs mixture in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle parsley over each layer.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve immediately.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: Let water and all other ingredients (except mushrooms) come to a boil, mixing well.
Add cleaned, trimmed mushrooms and let come to a boil again.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes; cool thoroughly.
Let stand at least overnight.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Beat eggs very light and gradually, then beat in sugar.
Add cold water and beat again.
Add flour, sifted with salt and cinnamon, and fold in nuts and gumdrops.
Spread in a greased and floured pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix sugar, flour and milk until smooth.
Melt butter in 9 inch square pan and set aside.
Pour batter into butter.
(DO NOT STIR.)
Pour fruit on top of batter. (DO NOT STIR.)
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: maple peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend together the peanut butter and shortening; beat in the brown sugar and maple syrup.
Add egg and beat well.
Sift flour with baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add the first mixture, beating thoroughly.
Turn out on floured board and divide in half. Shape each half into a roll about 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap well in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Cut in 1/4-inch slices. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven for about 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Lightly brown mushrooms and onions in butter.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbly.
Stir in broth and cream.
Add in salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste.
Cook, stirring frequently until mixture boils.

title: quesadilla bread (sweet bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix the pancake mix with sugar. Beat eggs slightly in milk, then add oil. Stir together. Blend in sour cream or Parmesan cheese. Melt butter or margarine in microwave and add to mixture and pour into a greased baking loaf pan. Bake 35 minutes until cooked or slightly browned and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. About 20 minutes before it hardens, sprinkle sesame seeds on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Mix together the Cool Whip, milk, sour cream and sugar.
Pour over cake pieces in bowl; stir.
Mix strawberries and glaze.
Mix 2/3 to cake and stir.
Put remaining strawberries on top.
Chill overnight.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Mix with blueberries.
Turn into 9-inch crust.
Sprinkle lemon juice and dot with butter.
Put top crust on and pinch edges firmly together.
Prick top with fork and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: almond roca candy
directions: Put butter in skillet and heat until bubbly but not brown.
Add rest of ingredients except chocolate and cook over hot heat, stirring constantly until almonds are toasted through and sugar is light medium brown.
Pour into 2 buttered pans (10 x 15-inches). Cool and spread with half the melted chocolate.
Sprinkle with ground walnuts and let chocolate harden.
Turn and repeat on other side.
Break in pieces.

title: empanadas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil the water with the cinnamon stick until water is brown.
Mix dry ingredients first.
Add shortening; mix well.
Add water; make a dough.
Separate dough into balls. With rolling pin, make a circle
of dough not too big.
Add a tablespoon of pumpkin mix on half of the circle; fold in half to make a half moon.
Seal with a fork.
Cook until light brown. Enjoy!

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Butter a 2 qt. casserole dish and set aside.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Boil macaroni in lots of water.
Drain and set aside.
Beat 2 eggs into casserole dish.
Pour in milk and salt. Stir in cheese.
Add drained macaroni.
If milk doesn't cover macaroni, add more milk and stir.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until the casserole doesn't jiggle when you shake it.

title: 3-layer candy
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients and add the rice krispies.
Put in 9 x13-inch pan.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Cream 1/2 cup margarine and powdered sugar.
Mix milk with dry pudding.
Add milk and pudding mixture to creamed margarine and powdered sugar; spread on first mixture.
Melt chocolate and margarine and pour on 2nd layer and chill.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Store in tightly closed container until ready to make biscuits.
No refrigeration required.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Melt together the brown sugar, water and 2 tablespoons of butter for sauce.
Mix sugar and 2 tablespoons of butter, then add other dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Sprinkle nuts over batter.
Pour on sauce and bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: easy chili
directions: Saute the meat with onion and green pepper until meat is brown. Add tomatoes, kidney beans, bay leaf, paprika, red pepper and chili powder.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Serve as a thick soup or over spaghetti.
Delicious on a cool night at the beach.

title: roasted potatoes with garlic and rosemary
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place the potatoes in a baking dish together with the garlic and rosemary and season with salt and pepper.
Add the olive oil and mix well to coat the potatoes. Stir in the water and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour without touching or stirring the potatoes.
When they have a deep golden color, they are ready to be served.
(They may stick a little to the pan.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, sugar and margarine together (save 1/4 cup for top).
Press into 12 x 8-inch glass dish and bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool crust.

title: snow pudding
directions: Combine vanilla, milk or half and half cream and sugar. Divide snow between 2 chilled sundae glasses.
Pour half of topping mixture over each.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well. Cook sauce of milk and cheese on low in double boiler or
melt in microwave.

Melt butter and mix well with cracker crumbs. Grease a 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Spread broccoli in bottom and pour sauce over. Cover with crumb mixture. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate sauerkraut cake
directions: Mix in order given except the water is poured as needed.
Pour into two well-greased layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost as desired.

title: johnny appleseed shake
directions: Place all of the ingredients in a blender container.
Cover and blend on High for 30 seconds or until smooth and well blended. Pour into glasses and serve immediately.

title: fruit salad
directions: Save pineapple juice.
Mix fruit in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, combine Tang, pudding mix and reserved pineapple juice with mixer.
Put on fruit and mix well.
Chill.

title: chicken tacos
directions: In skillet, place chicken, seasoning mix and water bringing to a boil and simmering 10 minutes.
Spoon filling into bottom of each taco shell and top with garnishes.

title: banana-coconut dream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast coconut on cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Combine the cake mix with the whipped topping.
Mix as it comes dry from the package.
Mix with eggs, bananas, coconut, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican vegetable rice
directions: In a wide frying pan, heat oil over medium heat; add onion, garlic and rice. Cook, stirring until onion is limp and rice is opaque; stir in salt, cayenne and bouillon cubes dissolved in boiling water. Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Add peas and tomatoes. Cook over low heat, stirring just until vegetables are heated. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Prepare pie crust or use frozen.
Blend together remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: mom's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Stir in the pumpkin. Add dry ingredients. Stir in the Pet milk.
Pour into two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 350° until done, when a knife is inserted.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir together all of the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir the liquid ingredients together in a separate bowl and then stir them into the dry ingredients, mixing only enough to combine the ingredients thoroughly.
Less mixing will make a more tender bread. Pour the batter into an oiled 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
The top will spring back when the bread is done and a tester should come out clean but moist (not uncooked batter), but it may be moister than normally expected.
This corn bread is most delicious when eaten warm.

title: crunchy tuna salad
directions: Pour boiling water over tuna.
Drain and cool.
Add celery, carrots and onion.
Blend salad dressing and whipped cream.
Add to tuna.
Stir in potatoes.
Serve immediately on a bed of lettuce.
Yields 6 servings.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done, then remove from water (reserve 1 cup of broth).
Cook noodles in remaining broth.
Remove chicken from bones; add chicken to noodles and broth.
In saucepan, cook remaining ingredients (except pimento) together to make gravy. Combine chicken, noodles, broth, gravy and pimentos in a large baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until cheese melts.

title: quick mushroom sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Combine soup mix with 1 cup water; whisk to blend.
Pour into stock; mix and bring to a slow simmer.
In a jar with lid, add 1/2 cup cold water with 2 tablespoons flour and shake.
Add flour and water mixture to sauce.
Add onion.
Season with a little pepper.
(Add milk to dilute after simmered for 15 minutes if necessary.)
Stir constantly.

title: portuguese sweet bread
directions: Boil caraway seed in 1 cup water for 15 minutes.
Strain and keep water.
Moisten yeast with 2 tablespoons warm water; add 1 tablespoon sugar and stir until dissolved.
Scald milk (combined with water).
Add butter and salt.
Cool; add yeast and 1/4 cup caraway liquid.
Place 2 1/2 cups flour in bowl; add liquid.
Beat dough; stir in 2 1/2 cups flour.
Cover bowl; allow to double. Beat eggs, take out 2 tablespoons; add remaining sugar to beaten eggs.
Stir into dough.
Add 2 to 3 cups flour; divide dough into round loaves.
Cover and allow to double.
Brush surface with egg. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Deep fry until brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Cook green beans, adding bouillon cubes. In a skillet, saute onions and mushrooms with margarine and soy sauce. Stir into beans. Lightly toast almonds in oven and pour over beans. Simmer on low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: firehouse meat loaf(made on the spot)
directions: Mix well, forming 2 loaves or 3 will take shorter baking time. Place in baking dish, small roaster or foil pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, the last half hour uncovered, or bake until brown on top.
Drain excess grease.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix yogurt and mayonnaise in medium bowl until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate any remaining dip.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: holiday salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Heat juice and mix in dry jello.
Cool.
Add other ingredients and turn into mold. Chill until firm.

title: bleu cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Bleu cheese, onion, celery, Miracle Whip and cayenne pepper.
Form a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: gingerbread people
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, molasses and water. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Heat oven to 350°.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on floured board. Cut with floured gingerbread cutter or other favorite shaped cutter.
Place about 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until no indentation remains when touched, 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Decorate with colored frosting and candies, if desired.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.
Has 180 calories per cookie.

title: caramel pudding
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.

title: tomato risotto with shrimp(serves 2)
directions: Spray low, wide and shallow microwave casserole with cooking spray.
Add chopped onion and garlic; microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes until onion is tender.
Add rice and stir to combine. Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Add chicken stock and stir to combine.
Cook at 50% power for 10 minutes.
Stir well; add chopped tomatoes.
Cook an additional 10 minutes at 50% power.
Stir again and continue cooking at 50% power until almost all the liquid is absorbed.
Add shrimp and cook for 4 minutes or until shrimp are cooked through.
Stir in grated lemon peel and Parmesan cheese. Let sit for a few minutes to melt the cheese.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix cake.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Cool.
Ice with the Cool Whip and pudding mix, then sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: ho ho bars
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Put in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: onion mushroom gravy
directions: In medium saucepan, combine soup mix and flour, stir in water.
