Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to medium and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes or until gravy is thickened.
Makes 2 cups.

title: beef at its best
directions: Line baking pan with aluminum foil.
Sprinkle some of the onion flakes.
Place beef brisket in middle and surround with rest of onion flakes.
Enclose aluminum foil, folding over all sides tightly.
Place in a 250° oven for 7 hours, until tender and flavorful.
Always a favorite and so easy, too!

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour with salt and pepper; pound mixture thoroughly into both sides of steak.
Cut into serving pieces.
Preheat skillet, uncovered, at 375°.
Melt shortening.
Brown steak for 5 minutes per side.
Combine vegetables and water.
Pour over steak; cover with vent closed.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Reduce heat to "warm" for serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 cup onions.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion; bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tomato chutney
directions: Peel
and
chop
tomatoes,
pears,
peaches, apples and onions.
Mix
all ingredients and boil until thick.
Pour into sterilized jars to
within 1/2 inch of top. Put on cap.
Screw band firmly
tight.
Process
in boiling water bath 5 minutes. Yields 12 pints.

title: bill kellar's corn-on-the-cob
directions: Peel back husk on corn and remove the silk.
Rub butter all over ear of corn.
Pull husk back over the buttered corn.
Cover ear with plastic wrap, but leave the ends of the wrap open. Microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes per ear.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at room temperature; cream and gradually add pineapple (well drained) until smooth.
Add pepper, onion, salt and 1 cup pecans.
Mix well.
Chill mixture several hours and then form into one large or 2 small balls.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Chill until serving time.

title: cowboy baked beans
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Add salt and pepper.
Mix in all other ingredients; stir well.
Bake for 30 minutes, uncovered, in a 350° oven.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Then beat in flour and sugars until well blended.
Blend in melted butter; stir in chips and walnuts. Pour into the pie shell.

title: grilled island corn(microwave)
directions: Combine corn and water in a 2-quart rectangular microwave dish.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap, turned back slightly on one side.
Cook on High (100% power) until just tender, 8 to 11 minutes, turning ears over and rotating dish after 4 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Then add can of mandarin oranges, juice included.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely and frost.

title: fritos bean hot dish
directions: Set aside one cup of corn chips.
Coarsely crush remaining chips.
Mix coarsely crushed chips with next 6 ingredients.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes. Spoon sour cream on top of casserole and sprinkle cheese over. Spread remaining chips around edge.
Return to oven, uncovered, for 3 more minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Beat all of this together with mixer until light and fluffy. Fold in 1 medium cucumber, chopped.
Turn into greased mold.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush saltine crackers.
Set aside.
Stir jellied cranberry sauce to eliminate chunks.
Layer in pan or bowl; first, crushed crackers followed by spoons of Cool Whip around on that and sprinkle with more cracker crumbs.
Spread spoonfuls of the cranberry sauce around on top of that.
Keep repeating this, whip cream, cracker crumbs and cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle top with miniature marshmallows.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth and then add sugar, vanilla and Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into a ready-made graham cracker crust. Put into refrigerator and let cool.

title: wonder fudge
directions: Measure margarine, chocolate morsels, corn syrup and vanilla into large saucepan.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix in sugar.
Add Rice Krispies cereal; stir until evenly coated.
Press mixture evenly in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm. Cut into squares.
Yields 25 squares.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Optional:
Substitute fresh broccoli and cauliflower for the peas and corn.

title: quick tuna salad
directions: Mix all items except shoestring potatoes.
Cool in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Just before serving, add shoestrings and serve immediately.
Cheese cubes can be added for extra protein.
This salad does not keep well so I make enough to serve once then repeat if necessary or save for leftovers.

title: easy chip cookies
directions: With mixer, beat oleo and peanut butter.
Add both sugars, then add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and baking soda until blended.
Use teaspoon.
Drop and flatten out. Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
Don't grease cookie sheets.

title: velma's favorite corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients; pour into a 10 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with vegetables, milk and buttermilk.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In a pan, mix Cheez Whiz, mushroom soup, onions and broccoli. Cook over low heat until well blended.
Add rice.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef-vegetable soup
directions: Saute meat and onions in butter until well browned.
Add tomatoes, water, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, bay leaf, celery and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and thyme.
Bring to a boil again. Simmer for 15 minutes longer.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Save 1 3/4 cups juice.
Use 1 3/4 cups juice with eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Cook this until thick.
Pour over macaroni in bowl.
Let stand in fridge overnight.
Next day, add fruit and cherries (discard juice), Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix and eat.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Poke holes in cooled cake and pour Jello mixed with waters into holes.
Combine Cool Whip with pudding mix, milk, vanilla and orange extract.
Beat until thoroughly mixed and thickened. Spread evenly over cake and refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: sticky buns
directions: Mix together milk, potatoes, sugar and salt.
Add the dry yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add 3/4 cup butter.
Next, add flour to make a soft dough.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
(Should double in size.)

title: norma walker's ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together, then blend in coconut, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Make a syrup of the vinegar, sugar and oil.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Drain sauerkraut; rinse in water and drain well. Add celery, peppers, onion and pimento to sauerkraut.
Pour syrup over all.
Mix together and refrigerate a day or two before serving.
Keep covered.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
It is a sweet-sour taste and very tasty.

title: hearty tomato soup
directions: In heavy pot saute garlic, onion and carrot in oil.
Add flour and rice and saute until rice is a little toasty.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, oregano and basil.
Cook until rice is done, 15 to 45 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add milk and butter.

title: pam's crescent roll cheese danish
directions: Press 1 can crescent rolls in bottom of large, greased pan. For the middle mix cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and beaten egg yolk.
Spread on rolls.
Top with another can of crescent rolls and brush with beaten egg white.
Top with a mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped pecans.
Let sit before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: oatmeal fudge bars
directions: Generously grease 10 x 15 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cream 1 cup margarine with sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix in oats, flour, vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Stir in
1 cup walnuts.
Set aside. Combine milk and chocolate in top of double boiler set over hot water and stir until chocolate melts.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon 2/3 of oat mixture into prepared pan, compacting with fork.
Spread chocolate mixture over top.
Crumble remaining oat mixture over chocolate and spread with fork.
Bake until golden, 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil; cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: autumn chili bake
directions: Cook and drain rigatoni.
In a large skillet, brown beef and drain.
Add onion, peppers and spices.
Cook until onion is tender. Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and water; simmer for 5 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, toss rigatoni with meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: syrup pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, eggs, syrup, etc.
Bake in 450° oven
for 5 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until firm.

title: uncooked cucumber relish
directions: Grind all peppers and onions with fine blade of grinder. Sprinkle salt over same and let it stand overnight.
Drain well and add remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
This makes 5 pints.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix macaroni, cream of mushroom and tuna.
Put half of the mixture into greased baking pan, then place slices of cheese all other on top of that.
Pour the milk on top; gently separate macaroni with a fork so milk can flow through.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for the first hour and remove cover last 30 minutes so top can brown.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Grease and flour 10 x 15-inch sheet cake pan.
Spread chopped nuts in bottom of pan.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients, mix well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into 1/8-inch hot Crisco.
Flatten patties.
Cook until golden brown on both sides.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Spoon crabmeat stuffing evenly into the fish cavity.
Place fish in a lightly greased baking pan.
Combine butter and 3 tablespoons lemon juice; drizzle over fish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: toasted almond spread
directions: *To toast almonds, put in
400° oven for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: chipmunk pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and add egg and apples.
Fold in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour mixture into lightly greased pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: spicy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, eggs, milk, sweetener, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in gelatin softened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Let cool.
Chill until partially set and pour in pie shell.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.
(One vegetable, 1/2 milk and 1/2 fat for diabetics.)

title: cheese soup
directions: Chop all vegetables. Dissolve bouillon cubes in water and add veggies.
Cook 1 1/2 hours.
When veggies are tender, stir in Velveeta and simmer gently to melt cheese.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Blend together butter, flour and salt; add milk and cook until thick.
Add cheese.
Then blend with macaroni.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for just a little while.
Can add a little more milk.

title: classic tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and serve.

title: strawberry candy
directions: Mix milk, Jell-O, nuts, vanilla and coconut well.
Chill at least 1 hour; shape like a strawberry.
Roll in red sugar; add dyed slivered almonds for stems.
To dye almonds, place in jar with a few drops green food color and a teaspoon of water.
Shake well, pour onto paper towel to let dry.

title: swedish ham balls in brown sauce
directions: Combine meats and the next 3 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Form into small balls.
Place in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over meat balls. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour, basting frequently.
Makes 16 balls or more depending on how large one makes each ball.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 375° until brown (20 minutes).

title: rice meat balls
directions: Combine
Minute
rice
(right
from the box) with beef, egg, onion,
seasoned
salt
and 1/2 cup of tomato juice.
Mix and shape
into
balls and place in skillet.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of seasoned
salt to juice and pour over meat balls.
Bring to a boil,
reduce
heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: no-bake cookies(great for children)
directions: You will need a plastic or metal mixing bowl and a stirring spoon.

title: creamy corn and broccoli chowder
directions: Melt margarine in 3 quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook and stir three minutes.
Stir in water; heat to boiling.
Stir in dry potatoes; cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in broccoli, corn, salt, garlic powder, and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Simmer about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Stir in half and half.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or just until hot.

title: bacon fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain fat from pan.
Set bacon aside. Beat eggs lightly and scramble in frypan, breaking up large pieces. Remove from pan.
Heat oil in wok or large frypan and add cooked rice.
Stir-fry a few minutes, then add soy sauce, salt, eggs, green onions and bacon.
Heat through.
Freezes well.
Serves 4.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine frozen hash browns, onion, broth and water in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes. Stir in cream of celery and cream of chicken soups and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour; add sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, water, grated rind or orange extract.
Beat with a spoon until smooth.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar.
Beat until whites form very stiff peaks.
Do not underbeat.
Pour egg yolk mixture gradually over beaten whites; fold just until blended.
Do not stir.
Pour into 10 x 4-inch ungreased tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes in slow moderate (325°) oven. Then increase to 350° and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Remove from oven, loosen sides and tube.
Turn pan upside down.
Take out of the pan.
Loosen bottom of cake and put on a plate.
Ice with favorite icing. Serves about 25.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix well. Freeze until slushy and serve with some ginger ale in a glass.

title: whole wheat cake
directions: Combine egg, shortening and milk.
Blend sugar, salt and baking powder with whole wheat flour.
Beat until smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: hot butterscotch punch
directions: Caramelize (melt) brown sugar, over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add water and bring to boiling.
Add butter and cook several minutes.
Add milk and heat, not allowing to boil, stirring constantly.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour in mugs with dollop of whipped cream sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuit
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add raisins and half and half.
Follow usual biscuit procedure.
Ice with powdered sugar glaze.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine first 12 ingredients in blender. Blend until smooth. Wash, tear and dry romaine and chill.
Place romaine in large salad bowl and mix with dressing.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat.
Fry bacon and cut into pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Microwave for 20 minutes.

title: crab quiche
directions: Sprinkle cheese into pie shell.
Beat eggs.
Mix with half and half and seasonings.
Pour over cheese.
Sprinkle crab meat over pie.
Bake 35 minutes at 375° until firm and knife, when inserted in center, comes out clean.

title: peanut patty
directions: Put sugar, water and Karo syrup in pan and bring to boil, then add food coloring and peanuts.
When it begins to boil again, cook at medium heat for 40 minutes.
Remove from heat, add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until thick, then spread into patties.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs lightly in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate fudge meringue pie
directions: Cook and stir until thick (4 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray muffin pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Use foil liners.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 425° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven; reduce heat to 400°. Cover the bottom of pie crust with tomato slices and sprinkle with salt, pepper, basil and chives. Thoroughly combine the mayonnaise and cheese. Carefully spread this mixture over the tomato slices, making sure to seal the edges of the pie crust completely. Bake for 35 minutes.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Combine.
Roll mixture in balls.
Bake 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
Shake a few at a time in paper bag containing confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: dot's impossible pie
directions: Melt
butter
or
margarine.
Add all other ingredients and beat.
Put in large pie pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350°.
Grease an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan or line pan with heavy-duty aluminum foil, leaving 4-inch overhang all around so you will be able to remove loaf from pan.
Grease foil.
Set pan aside.
Combine ground chuck, pork, breadcrumbs, half of the tomato sauce, 1 egg, oregano, basil and garlic powder in large bowl; mix well.
Pack into prepared pan.
Combine cottage cheese, 1/4 cup of the Mozzarella and remaining egg in small bowl; stir together.
Spread over meat mixture.
Top with remaining tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.
Serve loaf directly from pan or let cool at room temperature until topping is set, about 30 minutes, then lift loaf out of pan, using foil overhang as handles.
Remove loaf from foil and serve.

title: kathy golden's delicious potatoes
directions: Melt oleo and mix together, adding all ingredients.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: nachos muchachos
directions: Combine Velveeta cubes and milk in saucepan. stir over low heat until Velveeta melts.
Put mixture on nachos and top with remaining ingredients.

title: pork chops 'n stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place into shallow baking pan or dish.
Lightly mix together bread cubes, onion, margarine, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place mounds of stuffing onto each chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water; pour over.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until tender.
(Cover so they don't get too dried out.
Can cover with tinfoil.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: pasta puttanesca
directions: Heat oil in large, deep frypan.
Add onion and garlic; cook until garlic is lightly colored and add tomatoes.
Then add pepper flakes, olives and anchovies.
Let cook for about 25 minutes. Cook pasta al dente and toss with sauce.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: squash pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt on vegetables.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours. Wash and drain well.
Bring to boil white vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Add vegetables and boil 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Follow instructions to make jello.
Before refrigeration, add cranberry sauce, stirring until dissolved, with jello.
Add pineapple, pecans and apple.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Chill until set.
Allow at least 2 hours.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Melt butter.
In a mixing bowl, put sugar and butter.
Blend together until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat thoroughly.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheets, then dust with flour.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough, one at a time, at least 2-inches apart on each sheet.
Bake for 5 to 7 minutes or until the edges are golden brown.
With a wide spatula, loosen the edges of the cookie from the sheet.
Gently fold the cookies in half with the fortune inside.
Pinch edges together, then twist in the centers.
Makes 60 fortune cookies.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, orange juice and rind, brown sugar and butter.
Blend in mixer until light.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not too dry, then beat yolks.
Blend yolks into potato mixture along with half of the almonds.
Salt to taste.
Fold in whites. Turn into greased 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle remaining nuts over the top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in butter until well mixed.
Add buttermilk and dissolved yeast, all at once.
Stir until all flour is moistened.
Store in Tupperware container in refrigerator at least 2 hours before using.

title: artichoke squares(serves 40)
directions: Saute onion in half of the marinade from artichokes.
Discard remaining marinade.
Cut up artichokes.
Beat eggs; add crumbs and seasonings.
Mix in all remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool a little before cutting into squares.
Serve warm or cold.
Can be made ahead of time.

title: baked ribs
directions: Heat oven to 250° on broil.
Mix spices together.
Sprinkle half of spice mixture on top side of ribs and bake on rack for 2 hours.
Turn ribs over and sprinkle with remaining spice mixture. Bake another hour and serve.

title: fruited cream dressing(for fruit salads)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Makes 3/4 cup of dressing.

title: banana-blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Cream
sugar and cream cheese.	Whip whipping cream and fold in	with cream cheese mixture.
Layer bottom of pie crust with bananas, then divide and add the whipped cream mixture on top of bananas.
Next top off pies with the blueberry filling and chill. A
dash of vanilla extract could be added to cream cheese mixture.

title: batter franks
directions: Beat eggs slightly; mix with other ingredients.
Dip franks; let drip and fry in deep fat.

title: navy bean soup(bonnesuppe)
directions: Rinse and wash beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain; cover with hot water in large kettle.
Boil until tender with ham hocks.
Add onion and seasonings toward end of cooking.

title: viola's sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package on box.
When done, cool and split crosswise into 4 layers.

title: chocolate crisp pie
directions: Melt butter and baking chocolate together.
Cool.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add sugar and beat on low for 1 minute.
Add butter/chocolate, walnuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour minimum. Serve with whipped topping.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Melt margarine at room temperature.
Add grated or ground cheese and mix well.
Mix with hands if necessary to blend well. Add flour, salt and red pepper.
Do not grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix
together
pudding,
Tang and 1 cup pineapple juice. Beat 4 or 5 minutes with mixer.
Add pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges and bananas.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: linda's caramel corn(microwave)
directions: Spray inside of a large paper grocery bag with Pam.
Pour popped corn into bag.
In microwave-safe bowl, combine brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Microwave on High 2 minutes. Stir and microwave on High another 2 minutes.
Stir in soda and pour over popped corn in paper bag.
Close bag and shake well. Microwave the whole bag on High for 1 minute.
Shake well and microwave on High for another minute.
Shake well again.

title: spinach balls
directions: Defrost spinach and squeeze out liquid.
Blot on paper towel (do this early).
Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Roll into bite sized balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 80 spinach balls.
All or any part may be frozen.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook.
Put into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together. Add other ingredients and bake in a greased 9 x 9 baking dish for 40 minutes at 350°. Good side dish for pork.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown beef and onion in oil in large saucepan.
Add beans, tomatoes, water, chilies, beef broth granules, sugar and garlic; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
To serve, ladle into individual bowls and sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with warm tortillas.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cream cheese and crab spread
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat until creamy the cheese, reserved crab liquid, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper sauce.
Stir in chopped crab meat and turn into shallow, greased 3-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill before serving on lettuce leaf.
One cup fruit cocktail may be added to make seven cup salad.

title: dwain's rice
directions: Cook rice until done.
Add remaining ingredients,

title: supper-in-a-skillet
directions: Cook beef in oil until gray in color.
Add onion and celery and cook until onion is soft.
Add catsup, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, mustard and oregano; mix well.
Stir in macaroni and cover.
Simmer to blend flavors, about 25 minutes.
Just before serving, fold in cheese.
Serve hot in the skillet.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, Karo syrup and salt.
Melt oleo and cool slightly, then add to mixture.
Add vanilla and pecans.

title: bread pudding(club member:  neil h.)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl. Blend in pieces of bread, rolls or doughnuts. Pour mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it sets. Yields 24 servings.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture, until blended, at low speed.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop in round teaspoons 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Melt
chocolate.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a	time,
beating	5 minutes after each egg.
(This is a very important part
in making this pie a success.) Blend in melted chocolate.	Add
vanilla
and mix.	Pour into baked pie shell and chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and pepper; set aside.
Combine soups, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir in 1/2 cup of cheese, 1/2 of onion rings and potatoes.
Spoon into baking dish.
Arrange pork chops on top of potato mixture.
Bake covered for 40 minutes at 350° until chops are done.
Uncover and add the other 1/2 cup cheese and onions. Bake until cheese melts.

title: vanilla cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk and egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add butter and vanilla after it thickens.
Cool.
Add meringue.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate; mix together sugar, salt, milk and cornstarch; then blend with chocolate and let come to a slow boil, stirring until a pudding forms.
Beat eggs in a separate bowl and add several tablespoons of chocolate mixture, beating all the time. Add to cooked mixture, mixing well.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat to remove lumps, then pour into prepared pie crust.

title: banana chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, cream margarine and sugar.
Add and combine well the egg, bananas and baking soda mixture.
In a smaller bowl, combine flour, salt, nutmeg and chocolate chips.
Combine the two mixtures together gently until just mixed.
Spoon into prepared pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well; add eggs, one at a time, beating enough to blend well.
Mix the dry ingredients together (sifted). Add these alternately with the bananas and buttermilk which have been combined.
Add vanilla last.

title: butterscotch nibbles
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter, stirring frequently.
Stir in cereal until pieces are coated.
Stir in chocolate morsels just until combined, but not melted.
Spread on waxed paper-lined tray.
Chill 30 minutes or until coating is set.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
9 cups.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Add peanuts and pour over popcorn, mixing well.
Quickly form into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: vegetable medley rice bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch (2-quart) square baking dish or 9-inch square pan.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until center is almost set.
Makes 6 servings at 1 cup per serving.

title: susie's pink creamy slaw(calories: 119)
directions: Note:
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Soaking time: 1 hour. Chilling time: 3 hours.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll mixture into shape of a log.
Roll up in foil and put in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Sprinkle dry soup mix on bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch or larger pan or baking dish.
Wash rice and place on top of dry onion soup.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour milk and water or milk and chicken broth over chicken and rice.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 hours.
Watch carefully towards end.
Add water, if needed.
If browning too fast, cover with foil.

title: tortellini and spinach soup
directions: Cook and stir garlic in butter for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini; heat to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with cheese.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and butter in saucepan.
Let come to a boil. Combine jello and cornstarch.
Add to mixture.
Cook until thick. Let cool.
Add strawberries and lemon juice.
Cool and pour into pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: brown eyed susans(from sue)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape to marble-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Push one mint in each center.
Bake at 400° about 8 minutes or until golden around the edges.
Remove and cool.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: homemade chili
directions: Simmer all ingredients except flour 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add mesa flour 30 minutes before serving.

title: orange slice balls
directions: Cut orange slices and nuts in small pieces; mix with coconut and milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool at room temperature. Roll in powdered sugar.

title: caramel pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan; set aside.
Brown 1 cup sugar in skillet.
When fully melted, add boiling water.
Cook until fully mixed.
Add sugar mixture to saucepan. Cook until thick.
Cover with meringue, if desired.

title: baked chicken in sour cream
directions: Rinse and dry chicken breasts.
Combine sour cream, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt, paprika, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add chicken and coat well.
Let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight or for 8 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter, banana, vanilla, salt and nut meats. Mix until smooth; add flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ham scallop
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered bread crumbs; place in casserole.
Sprinkle top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: death by chocolate - "a cake"
directions: Prepare a Bundt pan by greasing and flouring.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: coconut-pecan frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan.
Cook over medium heat; stir until thickened (approximately 12 minutes).
Add coconut and pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add other ingredients and cook 1 hour on low heat.

title: oven barbecued steak
directions: Heat oven at 350°.
Cut steak into 10 equal portions.
Pour oil in skillet.
Brown each piece of steak on each side.
Transfer to roasting pan.
Add onions to oil in skillet and brown slightly. Add rest of ingredients to make a barbecue sauce and simmer in skillet 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over steaks.
Cover and bake 2 hours.

title: david's california quesadillas or tortilla stacks
directions: You will need 2 pie pans, glass or metal.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, flour and 6 to 10 Tbsp. juice. Add pineapple. Pour into greased pan. Spread crackers on top. Melt butter and pour over top mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pre heat oven to 425°F.

title: corn sticks
directions: Mix water and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Gradually stir in corn meal; cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese; stir until cheese is melted.
Cool.
Shape into 3 x 1-inch logs, using 2 tablespoons of mixture per stick.
Heat oil in large pot to 375°. Fry corn sticks (a few at a time) for 3 to 5 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towel.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and egg whites.
Put in a large buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Then add cottage cheese.
In a separate dish, mix together mushrooms, ground beef and spaghetti sauce.
Add to crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and bake another 5 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: adam's apple
directions: Empty filling into an 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Beat egg slightly; add vanilla.
In another bowl, mix the next 3 ingredients.
Add egg; mix until crumbly. Distribute evenly over pie filling.
Pour butter over top.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes, or until golden brown. Serve warm with ice cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef in shortening until all red disappears.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni in water until tender.

title: hobotee
directions: Mince meat.
Soak bread in milk and squeeze dry.
Fry chopped onions in oil.
When browned, sprinkle in curry powder and cook a few minutes, being careful not to burn.
Mix all ingredients with minced meat and bread, adding 1 egg.
Whisk other egg with milk, and after putting curry mixture into greased cups, pour some of this over it.
Stick a slice of lemon or bay leaf into each cup. Bake 30 minutes at 350° and serve in cups with rice and chutney. May be baked in casserole.
Serves 8.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Let butter soften to room temperature.
Cream the sugar and butter well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with whipping cream. Add vanilla. Start baking in a cold oven in tube or Bundt pan. Set oven at 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine rice, soup and water.
Pour into a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper chicken breast; place on top of rice mixture.
Seal tightly with foil.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: crock-pot beef and rice casserole
directions: Heat shortening in skillet and brown beef, discarding fat. Combine all ingredients except rice and almonds in cooker.
Cook on high 3 hours.
Add cooked rice.
Serve with almonds.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: very good cheese ball
directions: Cover dry onion with water and let set until all water is absorbed. Mix all ingredients together. Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Best if made a day ahead of use.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayo in a food processor, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill. Form into a ball and serve with crackers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Place in large bowl.
Add eggs (sliced), onion, red pepper, tomatoes and olives; toss lightly, then spoon mayo on top of salad. Stir in until completely mixed. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger supreme
directions: Brown ground meat.
Add rice, soup, water, celery and onion. Place in 350° oven and bake 1 hour.
Add noodles to top of casserole 30 minutes before done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cut up and cook chicken.
Remove from broth and let cool. Remove skin and set aside.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Saute onions, clove, garlic and green peppers.
Add tomato sauce, soup, olives, salt, pepper and sauces.
Mix chicken and spaghetti in large casserole dish.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Place in hot oven at 325° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: red snapper with leeks and chives
directions: In saucepan combine wine, shallots and vinegar.
Reduce over high heat until 1/4 cup remains.
Remove and add butter, small piece at a time, swirling the pan to combine.
Do not stir.
Season to taste.
Keep warm while fish cooks.
Season the fish and place in steamer with leeks; cook just until fish turns opaque, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place a cooked fillet on each plate; arrange the leeks on top, mounding them into a nice pile.
Spoon half the Burgundy butter around each fillet and sprinkle generously with chives. Garnish.

title: johnnie mazetti
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Let drain completely.
Mix with spaghetti sauce.
Add spices, mushrooms, onion, etc. as desired.
Simmer.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
In oblong casserole dish, layer 1/2 of noodles, 1/2 of spaghetti sauce and thinly sliced cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese melts a little, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken ala richard
directions: Parboil chicken breasts until done.
Cool.
Break into lengthwise pieces and place in oblong baking dish.
Mix mushrooms, soups, carrots, liquid, salt and pepper; pour over chicken.

title: refreshing punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: crab-stuffed sole
directions: In a 4-cup glass measure, heat butter 30 seconds.
Stir in flour, milk, sherry and salt, blending well.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring every minute until thickened.
Stir in cheese and set aside.
Cut fish in serving pieces and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In a large skillet fry hash browns according to package directions, remove and set aside.
In a large bowl beat eggs; add onion and green pepper and pour into same skillet; cook and stir until eggs are set; remove from heat.
Add hash browns and sausage; mix gently.
Place about 3/4 cup filling on each tortilla and top with about 1/4 cup cheese.
Roll up and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to
20 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with salsa if desired.
After they have cooled place in
individual sandwich bags and freeze.
Take out number needed, place on plate and microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until heated through.
Yield 12 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add sugar and oil, stirring in dry ingredients until moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup nuts and bananas.
Spoon into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove and cool.

title: never-fail beef casserole
directions: Brown meat. Drain and combine with rice, celery, soy sauce and mushrooms. Combine soup and water. Blend into meat mixture. Bake uncovered at 350° until bubbly, about 1 1/2 hrs. Serves 6-8.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: *May substitute raisin bread for white.

title: yum yum casserole
directions: Brown hamburg with onion.
Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients and pour into pie shell.	Bake in Dutch oven for 25 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes supreme
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones.
Flake salmon with fork. Add remaining ingredients, except for flour and oil.
Blend well and shape mixture in balls.
Coat with flour.
Pan fry in hot oil or until golden brown.
Turn only once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add dry seasoning mix to taste.
For best results, mix the night before.

title: ice cream
directions: Heat milk, but do not boil.
Beat eggs and sugar and stir into milk.
Add salt and vanilla to taste.
Cook like a custard until it thickens.
Put mixture into freeze and thin with milk and cream.
If a small freezer, use half the recipe.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix and drop by spoonfuls in deep fat until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together and mix in other ingredients and chill.
May be frozen and taken out about one hour before serving.
Also good frozen.
Some people add maraschino cherries to give festive look.
Other people add 1/3 cup of coconut flakes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep cool.

title: marinade for venison or other wild game
directions: In Dutch oven, mix all ingredients.
Add venison or other wild game; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes enough marinade for 5 pounds of meat.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice well and add coconut, crushed pineapple and pecans.
Mix well and add Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and place by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: malted milk rounds
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine, sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, malted milk powder, baking soda, baking powder and salt.

title: crock-pot stroganoff
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot; cook on low for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: Mix in baking dish, corn, bacon grease, sugar and evaporated milk.
Shake corn muffin mix over corn to completely cover corn. Melt margarine and cover top of mix.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat first 8 ingredients well.
Then stir in bananas and nuts.
Grease and flour bread pan; pour batter into it.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Add the 1 teaspoon salt and sugar.
Mix in the flour.
Knead the dough until it is smooth.
Cut dough into small pieces and roll it into ropes.
Make the ropes into the desired shapes.
Grease the cookie sheet.
Put dough on cookie sheet.
Brush the dough with well beaten egg.
Shake on the salt.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bean and burger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients except butter and crumbs.
Put in casserole.
Bake in 350° oven 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and extract.
Add salt, flour and nuts. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain and let cool.
Prepare veggies as for tossed salad.
Combine with beef, cheese and beans.
Just before serving, add dressing and tortilla chips.
Toss and serve.

title: beef roast
directions: The seasoning of a beef roast depends upon size of roast and personal taste.
Rub in red pepper, Season-All, salt, lemon pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Place garlic cloves on both sides of roast; place onion on and around roast.
Let marinate overnight in airtight container.
You can marinate longer if you desire.
I take garlic off the next morning but this depends on personal choice.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over vegetables.
Toss gently. Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Yields 4 servings.

title: italian sauce
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Discard the garlic.
Add to this the carrot, green pepper, bay leaf, oregano, thyme, basil, chives and parsley.
Mix well.
Add fresh tomatoes and tomato paste to this mixture as well as the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Simmer until thickened; remove bay leaf.
Better if made one day ahead.
Great canned!
Great on pizza or any Italian type dish.
Makes 2 cups.

title: lemon chiffon cake
directions: Into large mixer bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make well in center; add egg yolks, corn oil, water, lemon rind and juice.
With mixer at medium speed, beat until smooth.
In large bowl, with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff peaks form.
Gently fold egg whites into batter.
Bake in ungreased tube pan in 325° oven 65 to 70 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Immediately invert pan over bottle or funnel.
Cool completely.
Remove from pan.
If desired, glaze with Lemon Glaze and garnish with thin strips of lemon rind.

title: chicken primavera
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rack in middle of oven.
Cut chicken into thin 1 1/2-inch strips.
Spread olive oil evenly on a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Sprinkle on 1 tablespoon Italian seasoning.
Dice garlic cloves and sprinkle over chicken, too.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: fake lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Cook beef until browned. Stir in tomato sauce, sugar, salt, garlic powder and pepper. Remove from heat.
Mix together the cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, spread half the noodles, moisten with a little sauce, cover with cheese mixture, top with rest of noodles and then meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: oriental spicy slaw
directions: In large bowl, whisk first six ingredients together until sugar dissolves to make dressing. Combine dressing with cabbage and onions. About 4 hours before serving, crumble in 3 packages of noodles and sprinkle seasoning packet contents over all. Toss to mix. Cover and chill. Noodles will soften as they absorb moisture. Just before serving, add toasted almonds and sesame seeds. Toss to mix well.
This makes a large amount and is difficult to cut down so plan this one for a large family gathering or cook out. Caution, it is spicy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per instructions.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with the cheese.
Sprinkle crumbled crackers on top.
Dot heavily with more margarine.
Season to taste.
(Note: Crackers add salty taste.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cup brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in a saucepan or double boiler over simmering water.
Cool slightly.
Cream butter, peanut butter and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and chocolate extract.
Mix in melted chocolate.
Blend in flour and peanut butter chips.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top evenly with peanut butter cup candy pieces, pressing them lightly into the batter.

title: chinese chews
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Pat into pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Mix together the next 6 ingredients and pour over the first mixture. Return to oven and bake additional 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and cut into small squares.
This is a Swedish recipe. Very good and very rich.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown and crumble meat and onion.
Pour off any grease.
Add both soups and put into casserole dish. Top meat mixture with Tater Tots and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: fried oysters
directions: Season flour with salt, black pepper and cayenne and put in shallow pan.
Whisk eggs with milk in a small bowl and put 1 cup of crumbs in a second shallow pan.
Dust each oyster with flour, dip in the beaten egg and then in crumbs, coating completely.
(Add fresh crumbs, as needed.
If you put them in the pan all at once, they will get damp and won't coat the oysters.)
Refrigerate 1 hour to set.
Place a skillet over medium-high heat.
Add half the butter and oil and heat until melted and hot, but not smoking.
Add oysters a few at a time and saute until golden brown on both sides. Place on paper towels to drain and sprinkle with more salt.
Repeat until done, adding butter and oil as needed.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: special coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan.
Combine for filling 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, cocoa and nuts; mix and set aside. Sift flour with baking soda and baking powder.
With electric mixer, beat butter until soft; gradually add in 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Blend at low speed, flour alternating with sour cream.
Spoon half of batter into pan. Sprinkle with filling evenly over it, then spread remaining batter evenly over it.
Bake 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes in pan.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water then add pineapple and pie filling.
Let congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and spread over congealed jello.
Sprinkle pecans on top.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In bowl, combine soup and milk and reserve can of mixture. Add rice and dry soup mix.
Pour into greased 12 x 9-inch pan. Place browned pork chops on top.
Pour can of mixture over chops. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.

title: chicken and rice stew
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, bouillon cubes, water and seasoning together.
Pour mixture over chicken, celery, carrots and onion in crock-pot, making sure all is covered in liquid.
Cook on high for 4 hours or 8 to 10 hours on low. Add instant rice 30 minutes before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, onion, garlic and green beans.
Place in baking dish. Top with cheese, crackers and butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add onion rings.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: traditional pound cake
directions: Grease a large "horn cake pan" or Bundt pan with oil or margarine.
Line the bottom with brown paper and grease again. Cream butter, salt and sugar by hand for approximately 3/4 of hour (having butter at room temperature to begin with).
After the 3/4 hour hand mixing, start the balance of recipe mixing with the electric mixer.
Add egg yolks, beaten until thick and lemon colored.
Add beaten egg whites (beaten until stiff).
Turn the mixer down.
Add the flour, a little at a time.
(It will seem like too much flour, but it is not.)
Beat for 5 minutes; add flavoring. Bake in the deep pan, slow oven at 250° to 300° for approximately 2 1/2 hours or until a straw inserted comes out clean.
Do not fill the deep baking pan more than 2/3 full.
Would be a good idea to prepare a medium size pan for the balance of cake.

title: green pepper and rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburg with onion and green pepper; drain off grease. Add rest of ingredients; cover and simmer until just the right amount of juice is absorbed.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans and place into large bowl.
Blend seasonings, oil and vinegar and pour over beans.
Marinate overnight or 24 hours. Serve cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter, chocolate bars
directions: Mix margarine, graham crackers, peanut butter and confectioners sugar together.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate bits and Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk together. Pour on top of graham cracker mixture.
Chill overnight.
Cut and serve.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Melt Velveeta and add all other ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: scripture cake
directions: Mix like a fruitcake and bake until done.

title: one dish breakfast
directions: Mix milk and eggs together; pour over all ingredients except cereal.
Sprinkle cereal on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Note:
May be made day before and kept in refrigerator overnight. Great for large breakfast crowds.
Give everyone coffee and by the time they are ready for cup 2, your breakfast is cooked.
P.S. First one up slides this dish in the oven!

title: strawberry luscious
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water. Add juice from berries and pineapple to get 2 cups. If not enough, add some water. Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas. Pour 1/2 in bowl and chill. Put sour cream or Cool Whip on top and add remaining mixture and chill.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In large casserole dish, place 1 slice of dried beef for each serving; on top, place chicken breast.
Cross with strip of bacon. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: The night before serving or at least 4 hours earlier, mix taco seasoning and sour cream.
Place in refrigerator so flavors blend.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in crock-pot that has been greased with shortening.
Put sliced cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook 3 to 4 hours on low heat.

title: king crab chowder
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
In bacon fat, saute onions, celery and garlic until translucent.
Sprinkle flour and salt over vegetables.
Stir.
Slowly add stock.
Stir until simmering.
Add half and half, crab and bacon.
Heat (do not boil) and serve.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Combine all other ingredients.
Top with cornflakes and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen for later use but thaw before baking.

title: granny's banana bread
directions: In large bowl cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add bananas.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to banana mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan (for smaller loaves use 2 pans).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then on rack.
Cool thoroughly.
Serve plain, with cream cheese or butter.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt cream cheese with tomato soup.
Add gelatin; dissolve. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a bowl or mold that has been sprayed with Pam.
Chill until firm, approximately 2 hours.
Serve with Waverly crackers.

title: beer chicken
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken with margarine.
Pour beer over top.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Turn chicken; simmer 10 minutes and turn to simmer remaining 10 minutes.
Broth makes an excellent gravy.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Place berries in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Prepare biscuits. Combine flour, 1/3 c. sugar, baking powder, baking soda. Cut in butter. Stir in buttermilk, vanilla. Put dough onto well-floured surface.
Knead gently 5 or 6 times. Pat to 3/4 inch thickness. Cut 3 inch rounds.
Lightly brush milk over biscuits. Sprinkle with sugar. Split biscuits in half. Serve warm with berries and whipped cream.

title: sugarless pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg product lightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: cheesecake brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package, spread in greased 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Add sugar, mixing until blended.
Add egg and vanilla; mix just until blended.
Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture; cut through with knife several times for marble effect.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until cream cheese mixture is lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: phyllo-wrapped fried shrimp robson
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat 3 tablespoons of the butter and olive oil until the fat is hot and saute the shrimp, stirring for 2 minutes.
Add the Sambuca, garlic, parsley and basil (crumbled); cook the mixture for 1 minute, or until the shrimp are just cooked.
Remove the skillet from the heat and let cool completely.

title: linguine and clam sauce
directions: Heat oil and butter until butter melts.
Add garlic; cook until golden.
Stir in clams with liquid, oregano, pepper and parsley.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Pour over linguine.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Combine yellow cake mix with water according to package directions, adding 2 eggs and
stick
melted butter (oleo). Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake
pan
that
has been buttered and floured.
Combine powdered sugar,
softened cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Mix well and pour over
cake
batter in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Makes 2 loaf pans or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: con queso-cheese dip
directions: Heat a crock-pot on high and melt all the cheese.
Add onion, tomato and green chilies.
Add a few crushed red peppers, chili powder and salsa.
Use milk to thin down.
Turn crock-pot to low and watch so it doesn't get too thick.
This recipe is great for parties.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and let congeal slightly, then pour over the 2nd layer. Place in fridge until congealed completely.

title: brownie cupcake surprise
directions: Mix brownie mix using directions on box.
Fill cupcake tins half full.
Place Reese's peanut butter cup in the middle until it is even with top of brownie mix.
Bake, using directions on box.

title: cheesy bacon appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles (firmly press perforations to seal).
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese, onion and milk until well blended.	Spread about 2 tablespoons of mixture evenly over each rectangle.	Sprinkle each with bacon.
Starting at longest side, roll up crescent rolls and pinch edges to seal.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut into bite size pieces and serve.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream ingredients with hands; stir in Rice Krispies.
Make into little balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, oatmeal, cocoa and baking soda in bowl. Beat together butter, sugar and brown sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Add chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: rag cake
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Be sure and cut before it cools!

title: sands
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Roll into balls and bake at 350° (light brown).
Roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar again (store in tight container).

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to the directions on package.
Drain well.
Lay the drained broccoli in bottom of a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine the soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice; spread this mixture on top of the broccoli.
Place the chicken on top of the soup mixture and sprinkle with the cheese. Mix the bread crumbs and butter together and spread on top of the cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix altogether and store in glass containers.
Use 1/3 cup mixture to 1 cup boiling water or milk.
Delicious night drink.

title: chocolate cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and cocoa in a mixing bowl. Beat with mixer until creamy and smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spread into Ready-Crust and sprinkle top with chopped nuts. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: teriyaki tuna, halibut or shark
directions: Place fish in a baking dish large enough to hold the fish in a single layer.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except 1 cup of nuts). Roll into a ball and refrigerate until chilled; can be overnight or longer. Before serving, roll cheese ball into remaining chopped nuts. Serve with favorite crackers (Wheat Thins or Ritz are very good).

title: apricot nectar bundt cake
directions: Mix.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 50 or so minutes.
Insert toothpick to determine if cake has fully cooked.
Turn out while hot.

title: marzipans
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into whichever fruit you used. Roll in red, yellow, orange or green sugar.
Put on waxed paper. Refrigerate for several hours.
Insert green colored toothpicks and add green leaves with green tube frosting.

title: shrimp dejonge
directions: Blend all ingredients, except shrimp, together.
Peel and clean the shrimp.
Place shrimp on bottom of pan.
Spread butter mixture over shrimp so all shrimp are covered.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until shrimp are white all the way through.

title: red, red rice
directions: Add rice to a large pot of boiling water.
Stir once.
Boil for 12 minutes.
Drain into a colander.
Or cook rice per directions on package.
Char pepper on grill or gas flame.
Place in a brown bag and shake.
Remove charred skin and seed; roughly chop.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken and chop into small pieces.
In large bowl, mix chicken, Ro-Tel and soups thoroughly.
Place Doritos in bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Spread chicken mix on top of Doritos.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: chicken milanaise
directions: In a bowl, combine the cheese and bread crumbs.
Whisk the egg with 1 tablespoon water.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Dust breasts with flour, shaking off the excess.
Dip chicken in egg and then coat with cheese and bread crumb mixture.

title: hearty beef stew
directions: Saute salt pork in large skillet.
Place in a Dutch oven or stew pot with beef chunks, onion, garlic, bouillon, tomato, peppercorns, parsley and enough water to cover all.
Cover; simmer for 2 hours.
Add wine last half of cooking.
The last 20 minutes of cooking, add potatoes, celery, carrots, salt and pepper.

title: broccoli-carrot salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Combine with carrots, onions, raisins and mayonnaise.
Blend yogurt, vinegar, sugar and pepper. Stir yogurt mixture into vegetable mix.
Refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat, drain. Mix meat with soups, milk and taco sauce.
Layer the following in 8 x 12-inch Pyrex: large tortilla shells (soft), hamburger mixture, and grated cheese (Colby, Cheddar and/or Monterey Jack).
Repeat until you have 3 layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low calorie pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Cool with cold water.
Drain.
Chop all vegetables medium to small.
Mix all together.
Let set for 1 hour before serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add grated cheese and stir until cheese is melted.
Pour all but 1/2 cup of the cheese sauce over the macaroni in a buttered baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese sauce and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Serves 6.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Put first 9 ingredients in a large bowl and mix.
Place batter into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together until smooth.
Swirl this mixture around into the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat; crumble.
Add green pepper, onion, spices and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 15 minutes over low heat.
Cook noodles and drain.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put noodles in bottom of pan.
Pour meat sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle cheeses over the top evenly.
Arrange mushrooms over cheeses.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool a little and cut into squares.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until mixture makes a firm (candied) ball; test in cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Pour hot syrup slowly over beaten whites and continue beating until mixture begins to turn glossy and thick. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in a greased pan. Cut when cool.
(Use a large bowl to beat egg whites.)

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Take a half of cup of friendship; add one cup of thoughtfulness.
Cream together with a pinch of powdered tenderness, very lightly beat in a bowl of loyalty with one cup of charity.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion, mushrooms, bell pepper, bread and egg. Mix well.
Add Italian spices to taste.
Shape into balls.
Heat canola oil over medium heat in frying pan.
Add meatballs to heated oil and cook until browned.
Pour spaghetti sauce over meatballs and simmer.
Cook dry spaghetti according to package directions.
Serve with hard rolls or French bread.
Serves 5.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Put soda in the cup of pulp and let dissolve for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cream together sugars and shortening.

Sift together flour, cloves, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add egg to creamed mixture. Beat well. Add pulp alternately with sifted ingredients, then add 1 cup nuts. Mix well and drop by rounded teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: artichoke chicken
directions: Mix flour and seasonings; dredge chicken and brown in butter and onion.
Add broth.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: veggie burgers
directions: Mix together.
Add dry bread crumbs, if needed, to thicken. Shape into patties and fry in pan coated with vegetable spray.

title: lemon nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°;
stir together flour and sugars.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts and oats.
Reserve 1 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix 1 can of onions with all the
other ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish and sprinkle remaining onions on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade stand pie
directions: Beat lemonade concentrate in large bowl for 30 seconds. Gradually spoon in ice cream, blending well.
Gently stir in whipped topping until smooth.
Freeze until well mounded if necessary.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze at least 4 hours until firm.
Let stand at room temperature or in refrigerator for 30 minutes or until pie can be easily cut.
Garnish with strawberries.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: new river pralines
directions: In a heavy pot, blend sugar, water and butter.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Add nuts, still stirring.
Cook until mixture reaches firm ball stage (250°). Remove from heat; stir about 2 minutes and drop on wax paper (buttered) or in waxed muffin cups for uniform size.

title: crock hamburger casserole
directions: Place layers of the vegetables in order given in crock pot. Season each layer with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix soup with juice.
Add hamburger to vegetables in crock pot and top with juice mixture.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine water and rice; let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cook broccoli according to package directions, but add instant onions and butter.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat.
Add rice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz. Mix well.
Put in casserole and bake uncovered 1/2 hour at 360° or until mixture thickens.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef and pork together.
Soak bread cubes in milk and egg mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and add to meat.
Mix well with hands until blended.
Form into balls about size of walnuts. Brown meat balls in 2 tablespoons fat (or oil) on all sides.
When all are browned, add beef broth (about 1 cup) and cook, covered, until done, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit with almond cream
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a blender and process until smooth.
Cover and chill.
Combine fruit in a medium bowl and toss gently.
Spoon fruit mixture into individual serving dishes.
Top each dish with 1 tablespoon chilled cheese mixture.
Serve immediately.
Serves approximately 6 to 8.

title: steamed cabbage and smoked sausage
directions: Cut up cabbage and sausage in bite-size pieces in large pot. Add enough water to steam. Salt to taste. Steam until cabbage is done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Pour butter into a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Mix other ingredients well and then pour in baking dish and stir in with the butter. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in a big skillet.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Add raisins, cherries, fruit, pecans and walnuts.
Work all ingredients together with hands.
Pack in pan and let chill overnight in pan; then turn out on dish.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt the chocolate over water. Add the butter and cream together. Beat egg yolks until light and creamy. Mix all together well.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Heat
vinegar, salt, sugar, oil, mustard seed and celery seed. Pour
over cabbage, onion and pepper.
Mix well.
Put in jar
or airtight containers.
Store in refrigerator for a long time.

title: artichoke bites
directions: Cut French bread into 3/4 inch slices.
Line up flat on a large cookie sheet.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, and Parmesan.
Gently stir in the artichoke hearts.
Top each bread slice with a rounded tablespoon of mixture.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes or until top is golden.
Serve hot.
(You may want to cut the slices in quarters before serving for more bite-sized pieces.)

title: scalloped peaches
directions: Arrange a layer of peaches on bottom of greased baking dish. Place half of apples over peaches.
Sprinkle with salt.
Add remainder of peaches and apples and sprinkle again with salt. Spread brown sugar over top, then crumbs.
Add water last.
Cover baking dish first 30 minutes so crumbs don't brown too quickly. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Knead dough until smooth.

title: tomato sauce for spaghetti and lasagna
directions: In a large kettle over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook onions and garlic until onions are limp.
Discard garlic. Add remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low and simmer in a covered pot for 2 hours.
Discard bay leaves.
Freeze in one pint freezer containers.
(Just add ground beef to make spaghetti sauce.)

title: pumpkin chiffon pie with gingersnap crust
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites and sugar in a saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it boils. Remove from heat.
Place pan in ice water.
Cool until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar into a meringue.
Fold carefully into cooled pumpkin mixture and pour into ginger snap crust.

title: church supper deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in large saucepan; cover with cold water.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Remove from heat; cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cool eggs under cold water and peel.
Slice eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks.
Refrigerate 6 half yolks for another use.
Arrange 18 of the egg yolk halves on serving platter.
Place the remaining 6 egg white halves and 18 egg yolk halves in a large bowl.
Using fork or pastry blender, mash eggs. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Spoon or pipe mixture into 18 egg whites halves.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Refrigerate for up to 6 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Can make low-fat by using all low-fat ingredients.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry meat in large skillet until meat changes color.
Pour off excess fat.
Add onions, celery and green pepper.
Stir and cook 1 minute or 2. Combine all other ingredients; mix well and simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Beat all together until light and fluffy.
Put a vanilla wafer in bottom of each little baking paper cups.
Pour cream cheese mixture into paper lined cups (1/2 full).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with about 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling when done.
Chill.
Yields 18 to 24 cakes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix syrup and sugar to a rolling boil; remove from heat.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Pour over popcorn.
Let set; shape into balls.

title: church window cookies
directions: Melt chips and margarine on low heat until melted.
Allow to cool slightly.
Stir in nuts and marshmallows.
Divide mixture into two parts.
Shape into rolls on wax paper, and put nuts on top of one roll and coconut on one.
Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
While in the refrigerator, take out every so often and shape the roll.
Good and easy.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add enough salad dressing to make a creamy mixture.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute until onions are golden brown.
Put in crock-pot with next 4 ingredients.
Stir, cover and cook 7 to 9 hours on slow (high, 3 hours).
Mix sour cream with flour and stir in 1 hour before serving.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together grated apples, sugar, eggs and melted butter. Add milk and cinnamon and mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add 1 cup milk.
Add egg yolks; mix well.
Stir in 3 cups milk.
Heat mixture until it thickens. Add vanilla and margarine.
Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar until fluffy.
Spread on pie in shells.
Brown for 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save 2 cups of chicken broth. Debone chicken.
Break into bite size pieces.

title: gucamole
directions: Mash avocados.
Cut onion, tomatoes, cilantro and yellow chilies into small pieces.
Mix with avocado.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Place in container.
Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Pour over vegetables and place in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Can be kept up to 1 week.

title: basic rolls
directions: Heat milk, margarine, salt and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add egg and yeast.
Add flour; mix well.
Let rise in bowl until double, then make out and let rise again.
Bake at 425-450° until brown.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme together in a bowl. Spread between 2 Ritz crackers.
Melt chocolate in microwave.
Dip cookies in chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole with tightly fitting lid or foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: deluxe german potato salad
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Saute the celery and onion in drippings until tender.
Combine sugar and flour; add to skillet with vinegar, water, salt and mustard.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.
In a large bowl, combine potatoes, carrots and parsley; pour the sauce over and stir gently to coat.
Season to taste with additional salt.
Spoon into a serving dish; garnish with crumbled bacon.
Serve warm.
Yields 14 to 16 servings.
This salad is very good with any kind of meat. Also very good for potluck.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *I use about 1 1/2 cups of chocolate chips and no walnuts.

title: sunshine golden yellow cake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add the milk and the Crisco.
Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, the 1/2 cup milk and the vanilla; beat 2 minutes more.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done when cake springs back when lightly pressed with finger tips at the center.
Pour in large greased and floured pan or make 30 to 35 cupcakes.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cut or shred cabbage fine.
Combine remainder of ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add to cabbage.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream, then spread over corn in a 9 x 13 dish. Sprinkle cheese over top. Mix melted margarine and cracker crumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: crab soup
directions: Saute onion and butter; add remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered 12 minutes.
Sprinkle over potatoes, 2 tablespoons flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low heat 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Soak pork chops in salt water to remove blood (1 tablespoon salt to enough water to cover chops) for 15 minutes.
Pour pineapple juice in pan or baking dish (large enough to lay chops flat).
Place chops in juice (not covering chops).
Place 1 tablespoon brown sugar on top of each chop (spread evenly on chop).
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Remove foil; continue to bake meat, letting it brown for 30 more minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add eggs, then puree.
Sift dry ingredients. Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring
syrup,
brown
sugar and salt to boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add soda.
Pour over corn.
Spread on cookie sheet; bake 1 hour at 200°.
Serve hot or cold.

title: puppy chow crispy munchies
directions: Mix cereals and nuts with melted chocolate.
Place 1/2 the cereal mix into the powdered sugar and shake to coat and separate. Remove cereal and spread on cookie sheet to dry.
