Separate chunks to single layer.
Continue with other half of cereal mix. (I use a disposable plastic glove to coat cereal).

title: holiday cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars until smooth; add all little by little along with milk until all are blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Keep watch; some ovens vary.
Even if cookies are soft when taken out they will get firm.
(Soft cookies, less time.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into ball.
Chill for two to three hours and then roll in pecan chips.

title: beef hash
directions: Brown the meat, chopped onion and spices together.
Add chopped up potatoes.
Cook until the potatoes are done.
Mix flour and a little water and shake up; thicken the hash with this. Serve with crackers.

title: ham droolies
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Divide mixture onto 12 hamburger buns.
Top with a slice of cheese and bun top.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine all ingredients and press into a 9-inch pan.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Knead well. Roll into small balls (walnut size).
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
After cool, roll second time.

title: danish puff pastry
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Measure first cup of flour into a bowl; cut in butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork.
Roll into a ball and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 long 12 x 3-inch strips.
Strips should be 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Pour into hot greased pan.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours in 300° oven.

title: low calorie jello and fruit
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix milk and lemon juice and add to pineapple.
Stir into Jell-O and add ice cube.
Stir until ice cube melts.
Pour into serving dishes and chill.
Makes 5 servings, 40 calories per serving.

title: veal villa d'este
directions: Dust veal lightly with flour.
Saute veal in butter and oil for 2 to 3 minutes, until golden.
Add the warmed Scotch whiskey, ignite and shake pan.
Transfer meat to serving dish.
Stir in 3/4 cups of heavy cream and cook until slightly thickened.
Pour over veal.
Serves 4. Can add sauteed mushrooms.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pie filling in square baking dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Cut margarine over cake mix; sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Cream butter and sugar. Add one egg yolk at a time and beat well. Add 1/2 of the flour and 1/2 cup buttermilk and mix. Add rest of milk to soda and water. Add rest of flour, then soda and milk mixture. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into cake mixture. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs well, add oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat or stir	well.
Pour
into
2 loaf pans that have been greased and
floured.
Cook at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a glass bowl, layer lettuce, peppers, cucumbers, carrots, green onions, mushrooms and peas.
In a mixing bowl, combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Mix well.
Spread evenly over the peas to seal sides.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bacon.
Cover and refrigerate overnight; refrigerate at least 4 hours.
When serving, be sure each portion contains some of each salad layer.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add powdered sugar until smooth.

title: carrot-pineapple cake
directions: Sift the first 6 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.

title: beef and corn cheese bake
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender (use shortening if necessary).
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: instant salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese.
Add fruits.
Fold in whipped topping.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until frothy.
Gradually add sugar, one tablespoon at a time, while beating with an electric mixer.
Continue beating until the meringue is very stiff and glossy.
Spread meringue over warm, cooked pie filling, sealing at edge of crust.
Microwave on Low for 4 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; test for doneness.

title: cheese apple crisp
directions: Arrange
apples in shallow, greased pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add
water
and	lemon juice.
Combine sugar, flour and salt;
work
in butter to form a crumble mixture over the apples. Bake
at
until
apples are tender and crust is brown and crisp, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix butter, flour and 1/2 cup pecans until creamy.
Press down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool. Mix 10x sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Spread over top.
Add remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remaining pecans over top.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with hamburger.
Mix with fork just until well blended.
Form into 4 (1-inch) thick patties. Broil 5 inches from heat for 10 minutes on each side (for medium). In saucepan, combine gravy mix with remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring, until mixture comes to boil.
Serve over meat patties. Makes 4 servings.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a casserole dish and bake for 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk and egg yolks.
Slowly add lemon juice and beat well.
Place layer of Nilla wafers in pie pan and pour mixture over wafers.
Make meringue, using sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Brown meringue and cool before refrigerating.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and spread over loaf.
Return to oven and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: egg-drop soup
directions: Simmer first 8 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Blend cornstarch and cold water and stir into soup.
Cool and stir until clear and thickened.
Dribble in a slightly beaten egg, while stirring rapidly.
Serves 6.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix and work real good into a soft dough.
Pinch off dough to make a ball about the size of a hickory nut.
Bake in oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly brown.
(These keep good when cooked and frozen.)

title: alpha bits snack mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Store your snack mix in a tightly covered container.
Makes about 10 cups.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, egg yolk and sugar.
Spread on the bread.
Roll the bread up in a diamond (from corner to corner).
Melt 1/4 pound butter and brush on rollups.
Sprinkle with good amount of cinnamon.
Lay out on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy strawberry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour batter over melted margarine, but don't stir. Spoon fruit over batter; if any juice, pour over berries.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry rhubarb jam
directions: Let all of the ingredients come to a boil and cook until rhubarb is tender.
Remove from heat and add small package of jello.
Stir until thoroughly dissolved; pour into jelly glasses. Let set 30 minutes, then seal.
I put mine in the refrigerator, but any cool place will do.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place potatoes in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. In small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour margarine mixture over potatoes.
Toss to coat evenly.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until crisp, lightly browned and tender, stirring twice during baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Follow directions on package of Dream Whip.
Blend cream cheese and sugar together; blend both mixtures together.
Add blueberries and blend until berries are in small pieces.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: party pink salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple in pan.
Add 24 marshmallows over low heat; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add jello. Stir until dissolved.
Add whipping cream, cottage cheese and nuts.
Pour into pan and let congeal.

title: soft pretzel sea critters
directions: Mix the yeast, sugar, salt and warm water in a bowl.
Add half of flour; stir it in, then add the rest of the flour.
Stir and mix it until it becomes a sticky dough.
Sprinkle some flour on a cutting board and put the dough on it.
Knead the dough until it is soft and smooth.
(Add a little more flour, if necessary, to make less sticky.)
Roll dough like a snake; shape into sea critters (octopus, sea horse).
Brush with egg.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts mixed together well over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° covered until potatoes are done, about 45 minutes. Top with 8 ounces Velveeta cheese; melt.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in small bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary beater or at lowest speed of an electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes about 4 cups or enough for two 9-inch layers.

title: fresh pear cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and oil together. Add soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla. Add flour 1 cup at a time and beat well. Add pears and nuts. Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured well.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Fry and drain hamburger. Add all other ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes. In casserole dish, put in layers of hamburger, 1 can Cheddar cheese soup and 1 (8 ounce) package noodles or shelled macaroni (cooked). Bake 1 hour at 350°. Fifteen minutes before done, spread Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box using milk instead of water in the mix.
Bake in a 10 x 13 cake pan as directed on box.
Using a utility fork, poke holes in the cake while warm.
Mix well together the cream of coconut and the sweetened condensed milk. Pour the mixture over the cake while warm, letting it soak into the cake.
When the cake is cool, put the Cool Whip on the top of the cake and the frozen coconut on top of the Cool Whip.
Store in the refrigerator until cold:
best overnight.

title: copper coins
directions: Heat together vinegar, sugar, oil, tomato soup, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over carrots and let stand overnight.
Drain off most of liquid when ready to serve.

title: banana muffins(serves 18)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Combine remaining ingredients, add to dry ingredients and stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Cook spinach and save liquid.
Melt butter; add onion and saute.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Stir in vegetable liquid from spinach and milk.
Stir constantly; cook until thick.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Combine with spinach.
Place in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box, using low-fat milk.
Blend Cool Whip and pudding together.
In a large Tupperware container, place cookies, bananas and pudding-Cool Whip mixture.
Top with more wafers.

title: skillet sweet potatoes
directions: Melt butter and bacon drippings in a heavy skillet.
Add potatoes and water. Sprinkle sugar over all.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, stirring frequently until potatoes are tender and thick sauce forms (about 30 minutes).

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place half the cabbage in a greased casserole.
Add half of sliced potatoes and half of hamburger. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over layers.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening; stir in buttermilk.
Knead dough a few times.
Roll out on a floured board.
Cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush with melted butter.

title: spoon bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the egg yolks with an electric mixer at high speed until thick and light.
In a saucepan over medium heat, combine the milk and butter.
When hot, stir in the cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
When the batter thickens, remove from the heat and gradually beat in the egg yolks.

title: ginger date biscotti with white chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine first 7 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix well. Whisk together the vanilla, eggs and egg white. Add to the dry ingredients, cutting the ingredients in with a fork or pastry blender, as you would a pastry dough. Mixture will be crumbly. Turn mixture out onto a lightly floured surface and knead gently to blend the ingredients so that they hold together. Divide dough into 2 equal portions and roll into two 15-inch long cylinders. Place each cylinder several inches apart on a cookie sheet lightly coated with vegetable cooking spray. Gently flatten dough to a thickness of 1-inch and bake for 25 minutes or until lightly golden. Remove dough from the oven and allow to cool (on the cookie sheet) on a wire rack for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 325°. Slide each roll of dough off the cookie sheet onto a cutting board and cut each one into 12 diagonal slices. Return the slices to the cookie sheet about 1/2-inch apart (so that their cut sides can crisp up). Return to the oven to bake an additional 7 to 10 minutes. Remove from the baking sheet and allow to cool completely on a wire rack. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: royal plum pudding
directions: Dissolve the Royal raspberry gelatin and salt in boiling water. Add cold water, cinnamon, ginger and cloves. Chill until slightly thickened. Stir in apples, raisins, pineapple, pecans and dates.
Pour into 4-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Unmold. Serve with Brandy Hard Sauce.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with sliced or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mash raw ground meat into bottom of large cast-iron skillet. Cover with mushroom soup.
Top with Tater Tots.
Cook 30 minutes at 400° to 425°.
Remove and cover with cheese.
Bake until melted.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix preserves, dressing and soup mix together.
Pour over chicken.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken with wine sauce
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with mixture. Shake off and reserve excess flour.

title: single crust black raspberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar, cornstarch and gelatin until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in berries.
Pour mixture into crust.
Let cool and top with frozen whipped topping if desired.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Cream together with wooden spoon the cream cheese, cream, butter, parsley, onion, part of nuts and Worcestershire sauce. Form into ball and roll in rest of nuts.

title: oven baked turkey, ham or chicken
directions: Note:
Need roasting pan with a cover.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients; remove any grease.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
If too juicy, turn oven off and leave beans in to dry out.

title: farris five hour stew
directions: Put all ingredients in small roasting pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons tapioca over.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar over.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour one can tomato soup over; add one can water.
Cover; put in oven and cook for 5 hours at 250° to 300°. May be uncovered the last 1/2 hour.

title: carnival popcorn
directions: Mix the oleo, sugar, syrup and salt together.
Cook for about 5 minutes, stirring all the time.
Remove from fire and add soda and the pecans.
Then pour over the popcorn and stir real good. Put in a roaster pan and cook for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes, at 250°.

title: garden zucchini pizza casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt on zucchini and let sit 10 minutes.
Squeeze dry with paper towel.
Stir in 1/2 cheeses and eggs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, brown beef with onion. Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Bring to a boil. Spoon over zucchini crust.
Sprinkle peppers, mushrooms and rest of cheese over meat mixture.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in airtight container.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Toss boiled chicken in French dressing and marinate overnight. Next day, add celery and mayonnaise to taste to make a chicken salad.
Add nuts, if desired.
Place in baking dish and cover with cheese spread.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour or a little longer if not starting from room temperature.
Put can of onions on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sprinkle with light brown sugar and nuts on top; dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix thoroughly and sprinkle with awareness.
Bake in a moderate oven of everyday life, using as fuel all the grudges and past unpleasantries.
Cool.
Turn out onto a platter.
Garnish with tears and laughter and enlarged helpings of God, country and community.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Mix.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Mix.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Cut up rhubarb; put on bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix the 3/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour; sprinkle over rhubarb.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: peach and nutmeg tart
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together sugar, flour, peel and nutmeg.
Add peaches; toss gently to coat.
Spoon mixture into pastry crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until pastry is golden.
Cool slightly on wire rack.

title: cinnamon bubble bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Mix cinnamon and sugar and place in a bowl.
Make 32 round balls from bread dough.
Roll each in cinnamon-sugar mixture and place in loaf pan.
Cover and let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and hollow sounding when tapped.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix together the soup, mayonnaise, broth, lemon juice and salt. Add rice, chicken, onion, eggs, almonds, celery, cheese and mushrooms.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake at 375°, covered, for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: mmm good salad!
directions: Drain cottage cheese in strainer and rinse under cold water. Combine cottage cheese and Jello.
Drain fruit cocktail and add to cottage cheese and Jello mix.
Fold in Cool Whip and serve. Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: If potatoes are canned, drain.
If fresh, cook in boiling salted water until tender.
Peel.
Potatoes may be left whole or sliced as desired.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large skillet on medium heat, saute onion.
Add ground beef.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Spoon off fat; add garlic, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat; simmer for 5 minutes or so.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice zucchini lengthwise 1/4-inch thick.
Combine cottage cheese with egg.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Layer zucchini on bottom.
Top with cottage cheese mixture and 1/2 meat mixture.
Add another layer zucchini strips. Sprinkle flour over zucchini.
Put on remaining meat mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 40 minutes, sometimes longer if I use more meat and sauce.

title: candied carrots
directions: Cook carrots and onions until tender, not mushy, still firm. Blend margarine, cornstarch, V-8 juice, water and marmalade.
Cook until thick.
Mix with carrots and onions.

title: split pea and ham soup
directions: Rinse and split peas in strainer, then combine with stock and water in large soup pot. Bring to boil. Add ham bone, celery, 1 tablespoon parsley and tarragon. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer partially covered, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Helpful Hint:
Soften cream cheese in microwave.

title: leeanne's raisin bread
directions: In a small glass bowl, put raisins and water.
Microwave to a boil.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain raisins, retaining 2 cups of the soaking water.
In a large bowl, whisk together water, honey, milk, melted butter, eggs, yeast and cinnamon.
Mix well until smooth.
Add 2 cups of flour, whisk again until all lumps are gone.
Let this sponge stage stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Add raisins and 3 cups flour one at a time folding gently to avoid tearing the raisins.
Gently knead in the remaining flour.
In a large mixing bowl, pour enough oil to generously grease the bottom and sides of the bowl.
Put the dough ball smooth side down in the bowl.
Swirl the dough in the oil and then flip the ball over.
Let stand until doubled in size.
Punch down dough and knead out all air bubbles. Shape into 2 loaves and bake in greased loaf pans.
Pinch off all exposed raisins.
(Burned raisins really taste nasty.)
Let double in size.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Remove from pans after 5 minutes and place on racks.
With a stick of margarine lightly grease the entire crust of bread.
This helps prevent the bread from drying out.
Do not bag the bread until it is completely cool.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and spices in mixing bowl.
Make a "well" in center.
Combine milk, egg, oil and apple.
Pour into well. Mix only until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tin or cupcake papers.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: down home chicken soup
directions: Fry bacon; crumble.
Brown onion in bacon grease.
Add bacon crumbs and other ingredients.
Slowly cook for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix everything together.
Drop teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight in a closed container.

title: old fashioned apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350° and spray 9-inch deep dish pie plate with cooking spray.
This lowers caloric and fat content.

title: che che punch
directions: Mix everything in a large bowl and freeze.
Stir occasionally. When ready to serve, mix half the mixture with a two liter bottle 7-Up.
Do not put ice cubes in it.

title: green salad
directions: Start with 2 cups hot water; add lime and lemon jello.
Add crushed pineapple (not drained), cottage cheese and Miracle Whip. Blend with a hand held mixer; pour into a mold.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.

title: fudge ecstasies
directions: In a heavy medium saucepan, heat half of the chocolate pieces, the unsweetened chocolate and butter until melted, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and baking powder. Beat until thoroughly combined.
Stir in remaining chocolate pieces and walnuts.
Drop by rounded 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are firm and surfaces are dull and cracked.
Cool cookies on a wire rack.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: strawberry fudge balls
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until creamy.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs and preserves.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in nuts or sugar and chill.
(These will keep up to 2 months in freezer.)
Yield:
4 dozen.
May also substitute raspberry preserves.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and water until thick.
Remove from heat and stir in strawberry Jell-O.
Pour over strawberries and pour this into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip after Jell-O is set.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mash Ro-Tel tomatoes and set aside.
Melt butter and fry onion.
Add Ro-Tel, soups and 1 cup chicken broth.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Break Doritos and cover bottom of baking dish. Cover with diced chicken.
Add sauce and top with Doritos. Sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frosty fruit cooler
directions: In a 4-quart nonmetal container or punch bowl, combine apricot nectar, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, pour in carbonated beverage.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Serve.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Cook over medium heat until well blended, then mix with pecans and pour into a 10 x 7 x 1-inch pan.
Let cool, then cut into 1/2-inch squares.

title: white icing
directions: In a saucepan, mix milk and flour.
Cook until thick.
Cool.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add flavoring and continue to beat.
Add sifted flour alternating with 7-Up and beat well.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Test with toothpick.
Cool slightly before turning out on cake plate.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Chop broccoli into small flowerets. Peel and chop stems into small pieces. Mix broccoli, onion, bacon and raisins. Blend next 3 ingredients and pour over salad and mix; chill.

title: gone all afternoon beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a roaster pan with lid.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Crush 10 to 15 vanilla wafers and pour over bottom of greased pie pan.
Melt butter and drizzle over wafer crumbs.
Place whole wafers around the side of the pie pan.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add Eagle Brand milk gradually.
Add lemon juice slowly and continue to stir.
Pour filling over pie crust.

title: trash
directions: Blend first four ingredients and pour oil over and stir every few hours for 12 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a skillet, saute zucchini, onions and margarine.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a bowl, mix eggs and cheese.
Stir in the cooked vegetable mixture.
Spread the crescent roll dough on an ungreased casserole dish (or 10-inch quich or pie pan) to form a crust on the bottom and sides.
Thinly spread mustard on this crust.
Pour in the zucchini mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots.
Cover with water and boil 10 minutes.
Drain, cool and chop apricots.
Set aside.
Mix butter, sugar and 1 cup flour until crumbly.
Pack into greased pan.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sift 1/3 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs; add brown sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Add flour mixture, vanilla and nuts.
Add apricots to egg-sugar mixture.
Spread over baked layer.
Bake for 30 minutes; cool in pan.
Cut into squares and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: mini potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Scrub the potatoes thoroughly. Using a fork, prick potatoes in several places. Place potatoes on a baking sheet. Bake until tender, about 35 minutes. Transfer baking sheet to wire rack and allow potatoes to cool before handling.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: For Base:
Mix together pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Spread into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: brazil nut drops
directions: Cut each nut into 3 or 4 pieces.
In mixing bowl, mix together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheets.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes in moderate (350°) oven.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: pumpkin pudding pie
directions: Make crust of crackers and margarine. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown. Sprinkle gelatin over milk in pan.
Heat over medium heat until just boiling and gelatin is dissolved. Combine pumpkin, spices, Equal and vanilla in medium size bowl. Stir in dry pudding. Gradually add milk.
Stir to combine. Pour into crust. Chill. Exchanges:
1 bread, 1/2 milk, 1/2 fat and 1/2 vegetable.
Serving size: 1/8 pie.

title: jambalaya
directions: In Dutch oven, saute sausage until lightly browned.
Remove from pot.
Saute onion, bell pepper, celery, green onions and garlic in meat drippings until tender.
Add tomatoes, thyme, pepper and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Mix together liquid from tomatoes, stock and Worcestershire sauce to equal 2 1/2 cups.
Bring to boil; reduce to simmer and add raw shrimp, chicken and sausage and cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes until rice and shrimp are done.

title: oven omelet brunch
directions: In oven, melt butter in baking dish (13 1/2 x 9-inch).
Tilt dish to coat bottom with butter.
In large mixer bowl, beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in onion.
Pour into dish.
Bake until eggs are set but still moist (35 minutes) in 325° oven.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange prepared apples in well-greased 9-inch square pan or well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with water and lemon juice.
Spoon flour into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour measured flour into bowl.
Add sugars and cinnamon to flour.
Stir well to blend.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Spoon crumb mixture evenly over apples. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Add to sugar mixture; beat well.
Add vanilla and grated carrots.
Bake in three 8-inch layer cake pans which have been well-greased.
(It is very easy to serve when baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan instead.)
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When cool, ice with cream cheese icing.
Yields 3 layers.
Makes 15 servings.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage and onion into large bowl.
In small bowl, stir together sugar, vinegar, oil, celery seed and salt. Pour dressing over vegetables, stirring well to coat.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Stir until well blended. Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts. Pour into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix Equal, cornstarch and salt.
Add water; cook until thick. Add Jell-O and food coloring.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Line baked pastry shell with strawberries and pour filling over the top.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with whipped topping or whipped cream.

title: red waldorf cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add food coloring. Sift flour, cocoa and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Beat.
Add vanilla.
Mix baking soda with vinegar separately (by hand).
Add to cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: microwave country chili
directions: Combine beef and onions in 4 quart microproof casserole.
Cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, or just until beef loses its pink color, stirring once.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to mix. Cover and cook on Low, 35 to 45 minutes, or until hot, stirring once.
Let stand, covered 5 minutes.

title: simple fruit dressing
directions: Whip cream cheese and add marshmallow cream.
This sauce is good with apples, pineapple, oranges, strawberries and other fruits.

title: eye round roast
directions: Rub eye round roast with cooking oil and coat with spice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes per pound.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Add the jam and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serve with biscuits or scones.

title: 7 layer cookie bar
directions: In
baking
dish,
add
graham cracker crumbs to melted butter to
form crust.
Add chocolate chips, peanut butter or butterscotch
chips,
coconut
and nuts in layers.
Pour sweet milk over top and bake in 350° oven until chips are melted and coconut is brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked beans with bacon
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon and bring to a boil until heated through.
Place in shallow baking dish; cover top with crisp-fried bacon.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: freezer tomato sauce
directions: Remarks:
A cup of chopped green pepper may be added.
It may be desirable to scald and peel tomatoes.
Dried parsley flakes may be used instead of chopped parsley.

title: chicken with a difference
directions: Note:
More cinnamon can be added to taste.

title: barb's parsley potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Stir until creamy.
Gradually add milk and stir until smooth and thickened.
Add parsley, onion and 3/4 cup cheese.
Break potatoes into cubes and stir into sauce.
Cook on top of stove 15 minutes at medium temperature (covered).
When tender, place in greased casserole bowl.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
(Paprika can be added to top).
Cook in 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Season short rib with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place in Dutch oven.
Barely cover with water.
Boil (covered) gently for 1/2 hour.
Add 1 large onion (sliced), 1 teaspoon dry mustard, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 bottle ketchup.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.
Add water if necessary.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 2 tablespoons of Mozzarella cheese for top.
Spread in pan.
Top with remaining 2 tablespoons of Mozzarella cheese for top.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Eat with stone Wheat Thins.

title: crunchy cereal
directions: In a large bowl, mix together oats, nuts, seeds, milk and wheat germ.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and oil, stirring until smooth.
Mix with dry ingredients and spread mixture on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with vanilla and allow to cool.
Mixture keeps well if stored in an airtight container.
Yield:
16 (1/3 cup) servings. Approximate calories/serving:

title: chicken amandine
directions: On waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper. Use to coat chicken breasts.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix brown sugar, shortening, butter, egg yolks and vanilla with mixer.
Mix in flour and salt.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg whites slightly.
Dip each ball into egg white, then roll in nuts.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Press thumb into cookies.
Bake until light brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Fill thumbprints with frosting or jelly.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Mix flour and sugar together; pour over pineapple which has been put into a greased glass baking dish.
Add grated cheese over top, then sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot with ham or chicken.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg; on waxed paper coat chicken with crumbs. In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove; set aside.
In same skillet, heat spaghetti sauce to boiling.
Add chicken. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Sprinkle with cheeses and parsley.
Cover; cook until cheese is melted.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients including sugar into a mixing bowl. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into 3 pans lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple nut loaf
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add rest of dough ingredients.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Pour in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: spiced russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in an airtight container. Mix with hot water according to strength.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: In saucepan, saute onions and bacon until tender, but not brown.
Add chicken livers and cook until livers no longer pink, stirring occasionally.
Put mixture through meat grinder with hard cooked eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Shape ground mixture into oval mound with a nose-like projection at one end.
Decorate with slivered almonds to represent porcupine needles, use whole almonds for eyes.
If ground mixture is too hard to shape, add a little milk.
It is better to chill mold before decorating it.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Cut chicken; salt and pepper and place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle paprika and cover with following sauce: catsup. Worcestershire and vinegar.
Cover with foil; let stand, refrigerated, overnight.
Place in slow oven (275° to 300°) for 2 to 2 1/2 hours until tender.
Uncover; sprinkle with brown sugar and soy sauce (smoked salt).
Cook uncovered 10 minutes more.

title: stir-fry peas and mushrooms
directions: Mix peas, sliced mushrooms, salt and diced onions in wok or frypan with oil.
Add soy sauce to taste.
Fry and serve.

title: susan antonelli's spaghetti sauce
directions: Put all spices and seasonings in a bowl.
Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in margarine.
In separate pan, brown ground beef and drain.
Break up ground beef in pan with vegetables.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce to beef and vegetables.
Add bowl of spices and seasonings and crushed garlic.
Stir well to mix. Simmer slowly, stirring occasionally until desired thickness. Better if cooked a day ahead and stored in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: hamburger soup
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger and drain thoroughly.
Add onion, carrots, celery and cabbage.
Combine tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and beef stock/bouillon.
Add to crock-pot with hamburger and stir to blend.
Cover and cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours or high setting for 3 to 4 hours.

title: berry, berry good fruit whip
directions: Mix together and beat at high speed until thick and will stand in peaks.
Depending on kind of mixer, may take some time, but will stand up in peaks.
Use for pie filling, topping for cake or ice cream or to eat by itself.
Delicious and makes a huge amount. Great way to stretch a few berries to feed many.
You may use 2 cups berries and leave other measurements as they are.

title: english toffee cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, almonds, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cheese and sausage.
Mix well with biscuit mix.
Roll into golf-size balls.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: tabouli
directions: Combine bulghur with 1 1/2 cups boiling water in a bowl. Cover and let stand 30 to 60 minutes or until the grains are firm, but no longer hard in the center.
Shake in a strainer and squeeze to remove excess water.
Mix bulghur with remaining ingredients and chill for at least one hour.
Makes 8 cups.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until creamy; add lemonade and milk.
Mix well until blended.
Fold in whipped cream and blueberry pie filling.
Spread into crust and chill.

title: cookies made of yellow cake mix
directions: Mix
yellow
cake
mix and butter or oleo.
Add egg and milk. Mix
up
with
egg beater.
Add a little more cake mix. Beat
with egg beater.
Add a little more cake mix.
Beat with egg
beater until it gets too thick.
Take egg beater out and use
big spoon. If you can't beat anymore, then use your hand to
mix.
When
you are ready to put on greased cookie sheet, make
size
of silver dollar.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken breasts with sherry sauce
directions: Pound each half chicken breast with flat side of meat mallet to 1/4 inch thickness. Form butter into 4 balls.

Roll balls in mixture of chives, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper. Place 1 seasoned ball on each slice of Swiss cheese. Place cheese on chicken breast; roll so butter is completely enclosed. Secure with toothpicks. Heat oil in frying pan; brown the chicken rolls about 8 minutes. Place into covered, shallow baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 4 x 4-inch pan.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add milk and 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix together.
Add to melted butter in the pan.
Do not stir.
Add 3/4 cup sugar to fresh fruit; pour over mixture in the pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350° or until golden brown (about 1 hour).

title: one dish dinner
directions: Brown lean ground beef and onion.
Add salt, green beans and corn.
Place potatoes on top of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french fried mashed potatoes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Make into a ball and roll in cracker crumbs.
Deep fry.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla together; beat in eggs. Add chocolate and beat.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk.
Stir in nuts.
Chill for several hours.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar. Place 2 to 3 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 13 to 14 minutes.

title: deep dish apple pie(sugar-free recipe)
directions: Preheat over 425 degrees.
Mix apple slices and flour together, add Splenda and stir until mixed.
Turn in buttered 9 x 11 glass baking dish.
Dot with butter. Remove pastry from refrigerator and let set at room temperature until you can unfold it and lay it flat for cutting in strips.
After cutting in strips, lay over the top of the apples to cover.
Bake in preheated oven about one hour or until juice begins to bubble through slits in crust and crust is brown.
Best served warm.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Brown on both sides in oil and drain on paper towels.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Cream together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add grated zucchini and pineapple.
Mix with flour mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: caramel bubble bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Thaw the bread dough but do not let rise.
Break one loaf of dough into small pieces and make a layer in the greased pan.
Melt margarine, remove from heat. Add brown sugar, pudding mix, milk and cinnamon.
Mix until blended.
Pour over dough layer in pan.
Break the second loaf of dough over filling.
Let rise, covered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: layered parmesan loaf
directions: Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in cheese.
Arrange, overlapping, in 2 rows on baking sheet.
Bake in very hot oven at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: sweet tomato relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot and boil 10 minutes. Spoon into jars and seal.
Eat with vegetables or meat.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix cheese, half-n-half and butter in sauce pan over low heat until melted.
Place hash browns in 9x13 baking dish and pour melted ingredients over.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: yammy bars
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 c. evaporated milk.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix with 3/4 c. melted butter and 1/3 c. evaporated milk.
Take 1/2
the cake mix and spread in the bottom of a greased 9 x13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 6 minutes.
Then put 6 oz. chocolate chips over that.
Put melted caramels over chocolate chips.
Take other half of cake mix and put on top.
You may have to flatten with hand to lay cake mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool 1 hour.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through. Place potatoes in micro-safe dish.
Sprinkle with melted butter and chopped herbs.
Microwave 20 to 25 minutes or bake in oven at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix preserves, dressing and onion soup.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Use small amount of salt for onion soup is salty. Pepper to taste.
Pour preserves mixture over chicken and bake about 1 hour at 350°.
Serve while hot.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
May glaze, if desired.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Combine honey, butter and ginger in saucepan; cook over low heat for 1 minute.
Add the carrots.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring milk, rice, sugar and vanilla to a boil. Simmer for 1 hour. After you take it off the stove, mix 2 eggs and add to pudding. Mix thoroughly. Put in a rectangular pan. Sprinkle generously with cinnamon. Refrigerate.

title: just for kids: kiddie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour melted margarine in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a small bowl, mix brown sugar, flour, baking soda and pecans.
In separate bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in the brown sugar mixture and vanilla.
Pour this mixture over melted margarine in pan.
Do not stir.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Cut in bars and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 18 bars.

title: czech dumplings
directions: Combine
ingredients
with
just
enough
water to work dough into
a ball by rolling dough in the palm of your hands. (Dumplin' should
be
a
little bigger than an egg, about the size of a baseball.) Drop dumplings into pot of boiling water. After several minutes, take one dumplin' out, cut to see if it is
cooked
in the
middle.
If
raw,
cook
a little longer. (Don't overcook; they'll be hard!)

title: penuche fudge(one pound)
directions: Butter	sides
and bottom of pan.
Combine sugars, corn syrup, milk
and	salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until
sugar is dissolved.	Cook, stirring occasionally, to
234° on	candy
thermometer
or	until
a small amount of mixture forms
a
soft
ball when removed from water.
Remove from	heat and
add
butter.
Cool to 120°, without stirring. The
bottom
of the pan will be lukewarm.	Add vanilla;
beat vigorously
and continuously for 5 to 10 minutes with a wooden spoon
until
the candy
is
thick and no longer glossy.
The mixture will
hold its
shape	when
dropped
from
a	spoon. Quickly stir
in nuts. Spread mixture evenly in buttered pan. Cool until firm and cut into squares.

title: chicken custard
directions: Cook chicken the day before.
Take meat from bones.
Use stock for dressing.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add flour that has been mixed with a little of the broth.
Stir constantly until the spoon is coated.
Dice the chicken.
Make dressing to suit your taste.
Place a layer of dressing, then a layer of chicken.
Pour custard over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
This can be made the day before.
Bake when ready to use.
Very rich, but verrry gooood.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: In large roaster pan, cook sugar, buttermilk and soda to soft ball degree, stirring constantly while cooking. Remove from heat when soft ball stage is reached. Add vanilla, butter and pecans. Beat until mixture begins to thicken. Drop by tablespoon on wax paper. Allow for pralines to spread out.

title: german chocolate frosting
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir constantly; doesn't take long.
Add 1 cup coconut and 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add frozen juices. Chill.
Add 7-Up just before serving.

title: outdoor potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Place potatoes, onion and mushrooms in heavy foil. Dot with butter and season with Morton seasoned salt.
Seal tightly and place on grill.
Cook until tender.

title: country crock holiday cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a large bowl, cream Country Crock with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in dry ingredients just until well combined.
Cover dough and chill 3 hours.
Divide dough in half. Roll out 1/8-inch thick on a well-floured surface, cut with cookie cutter, place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove and cool on wire racks. Yields 5 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, and poppy seed. Mix well. In another bowl, combine eggs, flavorings and whipping cream. Beat just until mixed. Combine the two mixtures and mix just until blended. Pour into a greased and lightly floured 9x5x3 inch loaf pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of loaf.
Best served warm with butter.

title: stewed fresh vegetables
directions: In a 10-inch skillet melt oleo.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and cook over medium heat about 45 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix together flour, red pepper and salt. Add Rice Krispies, margarine and Cheddar cheese.
Roll in ball the size of a quarter.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Mash down with fork dipped in ice water.
Cook at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Freezes nicely.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Boil the berries 2 minutes. Add the sugar. Boil 1 minute. Take off heat. Beat 4 minutes and bottle.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Prepare cake mix according to directions; bake and cool completely.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, sausage, crumbs, cheese, onion and egg.
Firmly shape into large loaf in baking pan.
Mix remaining soup and water and put over top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: ruth parker's lemon bread
directions: Beat the ingredients together for 4 minutes. Pour into medium loaf pans and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pans and while still warm, pour over 1/2 cup powdered sugar mixed with juice of 1 or 2 lemons.

title: dogs in a blanket
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in shortening, a little at a time.
Add cold water a little at a time to form a ball.
Divide dough in half and on floured surface roll about 1/4-inch thick or less.
Roll hot dog in dough.
Cut off excess dough and rub cold water on edges to seal hot dog in dough.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together the chicken, soup, sour cream, pepper, basil, celery and mushrooms. Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Crush the Ritz crackers.
Do not substitute any other crackers. Sprinkle over chicken mixture.
Sprinkle the poppy seed over crackers and drizzle the melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can be refrigerated overnight or frozen for up to 1 week before baking.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water for 15 minutes; drain.
In saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in flour; then add broth, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Lower heat and add cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat; stir in chicken and carrots.
Spread in shallow 2-quart casserole. Spread stuffing over chicken mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: susan's brownies
directions: Melt butter or margarine and cocoa.
In separate bowl, mix sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Combine mixtures.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into strips and sprinkle with salt & pepper.
In large pan, make a paste with margarine and flour until it turns golden brown.
Slowly pour broth into pan, stirring constantly. Bring to boil; add salt & pepper; set aside.
Fry onion in butter, add meat and gently fry until brown.
Add to flour mixture and add wine.
Cook gently 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Wash & cut mushrooms; add to pan.
Cook another 30 minutes; lower heat; add sour cream.

title: canning hot peppers
directions: Wash and scald jars.
Wash peppers (leave whole).
Pack in jars loosely.
Mix and heat remaining ingredients.
Pour over peppers.
Seal.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze chopped spinach until dry.
Combine with additional ingredients and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Can be served with fresh vegetables as a dip or serve with Hawaiian bread, broken into chunks.

title: toad in hole
directions: Melt butter in a small frying pan.
Using a biscuit cutter, cut a circle from center of bread slice.
Fry bread until brown and crisp on one side, then turn over and break egg into circle.
Fry over low heat until done.
Use fried bread round to dip into egg when served.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in potato chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Saute crumbled ground beef, onion and garlic in large Dutch oven until browned.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well to blend.
Simmer, uncovered, 35 to 45 minutes until thick. Keep hot in Dutch oven.
Chili may be prepared a day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 cups.

title: german raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Alternately add flour and buttermilk and fold in apples.
Put batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.
Sprinkle following mixture on top.

title: red french dressing
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients. Blend well. Add vinegar and mix until sugar is dissolved. Add oil, catsup, garlic and onion. Blend well. Refrigerate.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cook peaches, sugar and cinnamon; bring to boil.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water; stir in peaches to thicken.
Spray oblong pan with Pam.
Pour peaches in pan.
Top with yellow cake mix.
Slice 1 stick of butter over top of cake mix.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; salt and pepper.
Add corn, sour cream and Accent.
Stir in macaroni; pour in a 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken sinora
directions: Put a layer of tortilla chips in the bottom of a baking pan. Then put in a layer of chicken.
Mix taco sauce, chicken soup and chili.
Put this mixture in the pan as the third layer.
Put shredded cheese on as top layer.
Cover pan with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute shrimp, onion and garlic in butter in large skillet until shrimp turns pink.
Combine water and gravy mix.
Add to shrimp mixture with red pepper, lemon juice and salt.
Bring to full boil.
Stir in rice and parsley.
Cover; remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: shoepeg corn casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients. Place in casserole dish and top with 1 stack of Ritz crackers (crushed). Ritz crackers mixed with one stick of melted butter. Bake at 350° until done.

title: froot loop necklace
directions: Tie large knot in one end of yarn.
Alternate colors of Froot Loops, marshmallows, grapes and Twizzlers.
When large enough for neck, tie knot in other end.
Tie around neck.
You have a pretty necklace.

title: pumpkin cookies(i usually make these at halloween and thanksgiving time.)
directions: Mix butter and sugars until creamy.
Add all ingredients in order, blending as you go along.
Spoon on nongreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Cook celery and onions with a can of tomatoes and the juice from the shrimp.
When celery is soft, add the shrimp.
Serve over rice.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs; beat well. Combine together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt, then gradually add to egg mixture until well blended. Spread in greased 8 inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes. Cool, cut into squares.

title: salsa zarren
directions: Dice tomatoes and onions; make sure to keep the juices.
Place in bowl with snap on lid.
Add ingredients to taste and shake bowl vigorously to mix.
Taste is best if allowed to sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: lemon pies
directions: Mix first four ingredients. Pour into pie crusts. Chill before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove and stir in peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Beat until smooth.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set about 30 minutes and cut.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine chopped candy, condensed milk, coconut, pecans and vanilla in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and mix well.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.
Stir in sugar.
Quickly drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 2-quart straight sided casserole dish by greasing sides and bottom well with butter, then coating surface with dry grated cheese.
Cook the spinach according to package directions.
Drain very thoroughly.
Add butter to spinach, stirring over heat until butter is melted. Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Reduce heat and stir constantly until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Parmesan cheese until completely melted.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Stir spinach mixture into yolks.
Beat whites in a large bowl until stiff peaks form.
Fold spinach mixture into whites.
Pour into prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Fontina or goat cheese mixture on top of mixture and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: cheese spread sandwiches
directions: Cook butter, eggs, sugar and vinegar until thick, then cool. In food chopper blend cooled mixture, pimentos, green pepper, onion and sweet relish.
Mix and then add Velveeta cheese and Philadelphia cream cheese.
Blend until mixture is smooth.
Makes 20 sandwiches.

title: blue cheese  popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Whisk together slightly, eggs and whole milk; add melted butter, flour, salt, pepper, blue cheese and chopped fresh thyme. Whisk all together. Chill batter for at least two hours or overnight. Butter small muffin pans. Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: super dooper chocolate cookies
directions: Melt Crisco and chocolate together.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg. Sift dry ingredients into mixture.
Chill overnight.
Roll in balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Pour into blender.
Blend until well mixed.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in zucchini last. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 55 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cut in tiny squares.
Makes excellent hor d'oeuvres.

title: aunt carol's pineapple angel
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cake mix with pineapple and juice.
Pour all into an ungreased 9x13 in. baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peas 'n' peanuts salad
directions: Defrost and drain peas.
Toss together with all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour batter into two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in middle of a loaf comes out clean.

title: baked flounder roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix together the cooked spinach, egg, wheat germ, nutmeg, salt and garlic.
Spread over the fillets and roll up like a jellyroll.
Secure with toothpicks and set, rolled side up, in a buttered baking dish.
Top each fillet with a slice of tomato.
Brush with oil and bake 20 minutes, or until fish flakes easily.
Makes 4 servings.

title: toasted pecan clusters
directions: Melt margarine in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread pecans evenly in pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.
Place candy coating in top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until candy coating melts.
Cool 2 minutes; add pecans and stir until coated. Drop by rounded teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Cool completely. Makes 4 dozen.

title: hungry boy casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, onions, celery, garlic salt and salt.
Drain. Add tomato sauce.
Cook until vegetables get tender.
Make Bisquick by adding milk.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Put meat mixture in biscuit.
Roll up.
Rest of meat goes with beans.
Put in dish.
Put biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° for half an hour.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Blend milk, sugar and tapioca (2 separate bowls for egg and milk mixtures).
Stir milk mixture into eggs. Place fruit into 1 crust.
Pour in egg mixture; dot with butter. Top with second crust.
Make slits in top crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: stone cake
directions: Beat all together.
Bake in an ungreased angel food pan, until cracks appear on top.
Bake 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Boil until tender.
Remove from broth reserving 2 cups.
Bring broth back to boil.
Add rice, cover and set aside for 5 minutes.
Bone and dice chicken.
Add Ro-Tel, soups and chicken to rice.
Stir well.
Add cheese and stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender, except coconut, and blend for 3 minutes.
Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° until done. Sprinkle coconut on top and let brown.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine lukewarm milk and salad oil; add.
Stir lightly until just blended, about 10 strokes.
Turn onto floured surface and knead gently 10 times.
Pat out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: milk chocolate and p.b. bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, combine peanut butter and butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup Nestle Toll House morsels.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar set overnight.
Cook and boil 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Jell-O.
Put in jam jars and seal with lids or with wax.

title: eggs in a frame
directions: Pull center from a slice of bread or cut out center with a biscuit cutter.
Butter bread generously on both sides.
Brown bread "frames" on one side in moderately hot buttered frying pan. Turn over.
Drop egg into center.
Cook slowly until egg white is set.
(Cover pan until white starts to set.)
Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Lift out with pancake turner.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew the hen; cut into bite-sized pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth with tomatoes and garlic on low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally from the bottom.
Do not drain.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Set aside for 30 minutes.
Stir in cheese and cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: squash-pecan casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender (about 20 minutes) in salted water. Drain.
Combine all ingredients except crumbs and pecans. Top with crumbs (mix with 1/2 cup melted margarine) and pecans. Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken new mexico style
directions: Place chicken in kettle with water.
Add onions, garlic, bay leaf, salt and rosemary.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Let sauce reduce to 1/3 of original amount.
Add sherry.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: parmesan bread sticks
directions: Dip bread in melted butter; then roll in cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until browned and crispy, about 10 minutes.
A great way to use crusts leftover from sandwich bread.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a glass pan, put rice and mix in all 3 cans of soup.
Stir. Add 1/4 cup water.
Stir again until all is mixed up well.
Place cut-up chicken on top of the rice mixture (have chicken salted and peppered).
Place in oven for 2 hours at 300°.
(The key to this is to cook on low so the rice gets done.)
Rice should be tender and chicken brown when done.
Delicious!

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together.
Put 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup.
Add hot water.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix
ingredients together and place in pie plate.
Bake in oven
at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until brown. Serve warm with crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs and add corn.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper. Stir in milk; blend in oleo.
Mix with corn mixture; blend well. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix, freeze and serve frozen.

title: cream crab and artichoke dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a 1 quart casserole.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and vent. Microwave at medium
for 6 to 7 minutes, rotating the dish a half turn after 3 minutes.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: dried beef logs
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll filling in small balls and wrap dried beef around each log.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat. Season to taste. Drain off any grease. Cover hamburger meat with water; simmer 15 minutes.
Add cans of Ro-Tel, corn and Ranch Style beans.
Heat and serve.
Double recipe if you're feeding a group.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In another bowl, mix flour, baking soda and baking powder together.
Gradually add flour mixture until it is well blended.
Add your bananas, nuts and milk; mix well.
Your batter will be thick.
Use loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until golden brown.
Turn out onto a rack to cool.

title: applesauce-red hot salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water (this takes time).
Stir until all are dissolved.
Add Jell-O to hot candy water and dissolve, then add the applesauce (I use Musselman's).
Mix well, then ladle half the mixture into a 6 x 10-inch glass pan and refrigerate until set.

title: christmas cheese fudge
directions: Butter a loaf pan. In a small bowl beat cream cheese and sugar with almond extract until smooth.
Stir in nuts, press mixture in loaf pan.
Cut into squares.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, combine filling ingredients.
Mix well and turn into shell.
Bake for 15 minutes; reduce oven to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool before cutting.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: chicken acapulco
directions: Saute onion in butter in a large saucepan until tender.
Stir in the next 9 ingredients, mixing well.

Spoon about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in center of each tortilla; roll up and place, seam side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over tortillas.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Bake cake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let get very cold.
Spread on pineapple.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour half of the stuffing mix over melted margarine.
Parboil sliced squash and carrots until soft.
Mix vegetables, sour cream and soup. Pour over stuffing mix in dish.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, margarine and eggs.
Add the next 6 ingredients.
Cook raisins until tender.
Reserve 5 tablespoons water off raisins.
Dissolve baking soda in it.
Add these and vanilla to batter.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gorp(r.a.'s trail snack)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a plastic bag.

title: nut sticks(muschkatzohne)
directions: Bake quick in a hot oven to 370° to 400° in greased pan.
Cut into "fingers" when baked.

title: jean's corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package, omitting the butter.
Add butter, Mexicorn and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.

title: honey sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook and stir over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens. Cool.
Serve with grilled shrimp, fish or chicken.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix thoroughly to a paste and toss with cooked, drained pasta.
Serve with Italian bread, if you like.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla. Blend well. Add zucchini. Sift all dry ingredients together.
Blend this and nuts into egg mixture. Pour equal portions into two greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours, depending on your oven.
(Test with toothpick.)

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Pat refried beans into 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased.
Mix together cream cheese and sour cream and place on top of the beans.
Mix taco seasoning according to directions on package. Mix taco sauce, ground beef, taco seasoning and water.
Layer on top of cream cheese and sour cream.
Sprinkle chopped green pepper, tomatoes, olives and onions on top of meat and finish with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: holiday pearl onions
directions: Drop onions with skins left on in boiling water for 15 minutes. Drain onions; remove skins and set aside.

Melt butter over medium heat; add flour, stirring with a wire whisk until well blended. Heat half and half separately to just below boiling, then add to butter mixture and stir until smooth and thick.
Add 1/2 cup of the cheese, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add onions; stir and transfer to buttered ovenproof dish.
Put remaining cheese over all and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix shortening and egg.
Put all dry ingredients in sifter and sift into shortening and egg mixture.
Add everything else.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes (approximately).

title: peanut butter cornflakes
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and margarine in large pan.
Bring mixture to a light boil.
Add peanut butter and stir until creamy.
Pour mixture over cornflakes in large bowl. Amount of cornflakes varies according to mixture.
Place Peanut Butter Cornflakes in balls on wax paper.
Refrigeration keeps them fresh.
Can put in freezer. Great treats!

title: wyatt's baked eggplant
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight.
Drain eggplant and place in pan. Cover with water.
Simmer until tender.
Soak bread cubes in milk. Saute onions, green pepper and celery in melted butter for about 15 minutes or until tender.

title: chinese slaw
directions: Combine peas, mushrooms, water chestnuts, green beans, Chinese vegetables, celery and onion.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Scald milk; add baking chocolate and stir until melted.
Sift together flour and sugar.
Add to previous mixture.
Also, add eggs.
Boil until thick.
If lumps develop, strain.
Add butter and vanilla.
Refrigerate.
When chilled, pour into baked pie shell and cover with sweetened whipped cream.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, Hawaiian Punch, and 7-Up together in punch bowl.
Scoop vanilla ice cream on top and stir slightly so that punch has a frothy appearance.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: 1st Day:
Take the 1 1/2 cups of starter liquid and place in a gallon jar.
Add 2 1/2 cups of sugar and peaches with juice.
Stir together with wooden (not metal) spoon.
Place the lid on loosely. (I put a thick paper towel over top of jar and use a rubber band.)
Stir daily.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, jello and milk together; set aside. In a separate bowl, mix strawberries, nuts and coconut together. Add 1/2 strawberry mixture to the cake batter.
Bake cake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: codfish cakes
directions: Soak fish in water overnight or boil and pour off water.
Boil again to get most of the salt out of the fish.
Break up fish; add rest of ingredients and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling cooking oil.
Fry to a golden brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in a deep bowl.
Top with the following:

title: pink surprise salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pie filling.
Add milk and stir.
Add pecans and fold in Cool Whip.
Can keep in freezer in covered container, 8 x 10-inch.
Cut and serve on lettuce.

title: prairie potato wedges
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 8 wedges; set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dip potato wedges in butter, then coat with crumb mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Pour remaining butter around wedges.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: In heavy pot, melt butter and saute onion, garlic and celery. Add salt, pepper, bay leaf and thyme.
Gradually add flour until smooth.
Cook 3 minutes. Do not let brown.
Gradually stir in milk with wire whisk, keeping mixture smooth.
Add clams with nectar. Bring to a boil for 1 minute. Add potatoes and bacon, heating until hot. Thin with hot milk if a soupier chowder is preferred. Remove bay leaf and serve piping hot.

title: almost chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine broth and gravy.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Drop in biscuits.
Carefully spoon them apart so they don't clump. Boil about 5 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and mix with 1 1/2 sticks melted butter. Spread in an oblong cake pan.
Cream together powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick of butter; beat until fluffy and spread over crust. Layer on top of cream mixture in this order:
1 can pineapple, bananas and Cool Whip.
Top with crushed pecans and maraschino cherries.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to boil.
Remove from stove and ladle over cut-up chicken laid out in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: fudgy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs thoroughly; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, stir well.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes (moist chewy brownies). Cool in pan.
Cut into squares or bars.
Makes about 20.

title: short 'n' sweet caramel bubble ring
directions: Generously grease a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle about half of the pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Set aside.
Stir together sugar and cinnamon; set aside.

title: corn custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, cornstarch, salt, pepper and milk in blender container; blend thoroughly.
Gradually add saltines, blending well.
Add corn and blend on low setting for 30 seconds or just until mixed.
Pour mixture into greased 2-quart casserole. Add butter (in one chunk).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour. Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: hello dollys
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Make a layer of each in order listed.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over this and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let set awhile before cutting. The longer it sets the better.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine; mix with powdered sugar. Melt margarine; mix peanut butter with it.
Add to your crumb mixture; mix well with fingers.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; pat hard and flat.
Pour melted chocolate chips over top; spread evenly.
After an hour, cut into 1-inch squares.
Should taste like peanut butter cups. Do not refrigerate!

title: blue cheese dip
directions: Combine 3/4 cup Blue cheese and remaining ingredients in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into a bowl and stir in half of remaining Blue cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve in a hollow cabbage head on pepper cup.
Sprinkle with remaining Blue cheese.
Yields 2 cups.

title: crunchy apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8x8 pan. Sift flour and salt together. Add egg, sugar and spice together. Blend with pastry blender until crumbly like pie dough. Spread
on top of apples. Drizzle with melted butter, and sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: fena's chicken
directions: Mix the sour cream with the soup.
Pour mixture over the chicken.
Top with the crushed crackers.
Pour the melted margarine over the crackers. Sprinkle with the poppy seed.
Bake in a 325° oven until bubbles through.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have butter and lemon juice at room temperature.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Mix sugar and butter together until smooth.
Mix baking powder and flour together.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time, into butter-sugar mixture.
Sift a little of the flour mixture over the butter-sugar-egg mixture and stir it in.
Continue doing this until flour mixture is used, beating well after each addition. Add lemon juice last and mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables, mix with chopped vegetables and pimento in large bowl.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans or 1 tube or Bundt pan.
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl and stir by hand until thoroughly blended.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moist. Add all other ingredients.
Spoon into pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for 3 cake pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours for tube or Bundt pan.

title: yellow layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round or square cake pans.
Cream butter and shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
