title: cream chicken roast
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Place in roaster. Dot with butter, then pour milk over it.
Bake until tender. Makes delicious gravy.

title: vegetable primavera
directions: Oil the bottom of the cookware.
Add the onions and place the leaves of the lettuce on top.
Add peas, beans, carrots, potatoes, zucchini and the herbs.
Add water, if necessary, cover tightly and cook on low heat for 25 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: a boy and a dog
directions: Go to the store and buy a package of beef jerky.
Go home and get your dog.
Sit under a shade tree.
Share the beef jerky with your dog.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add pumpkin.
Then add all dry ingredients, then water, stirring just until mixed.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans (or I use 5 of the 5 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans).
These make nice gifts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
For the large pans, less time for small ones.
I check with a toothpick.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix.
Before serving, chill.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder in a bowl.
Add shortening; mix well.
Add half of the water and knead.
Add rest of water; knead well.
Let dough stand, covered, for 30 minutes.
Preheat grill to medium heat.
Make 25 to 30 golf ball size balls from dough.
Roll out into tortillas.
Cook on grill about a minute on each side, until tortilla fluffs on the third turn.
Makes 25 to 30 tortillas.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in plastic bag, set aside.
Pour milk in large bowl.
Add pudding mix, blend well.
Stir in Cool Whip and half of crushed cookies and 1/2 of gummies.
In clay pot, cover inside with plastic wrap.
Put 1/2 of crushed cookies in bottom of pot.
Add pudding mixture.
Top with remaining cookies.
Decorate with gummies.

title: crab apple jelly
directions: Wash and cut ends off crab apples.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Pour juice through strainer into other container to make clear jelly.

title: jimmy carter peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend together the cream cheese and confectioners' sugar for about 5 minutes.
The longer you blend, the creamier the pie.
Add the peanut butter and milk to the mixture and blend again.
Fold in the whipped cream and pour the pie filling into the graham cracker crust.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses in microwave.
Mix in other ingredients and chill about 24 hours before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and milk and spread half of batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Melt together caramels and milk.
Layer over cake in pan, the melted caramels, the bag of chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop remaining batter on top by teaspoon.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well; add Cool Whip.
Mix well and add lemon juice.
Put around side and top edge of cake.
Fill top of cake and hole with blueberry pie filling.

title: best ever cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Beat egg whites until stand in peaks. Fold in with Rice Krispies.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.
Watch closely.
Remove from pan while hot.

title: pineapple icebox pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, cream, nuts, pineapple and salt.
I save the nuts back to sprinkle on each layer.
In casserole or mold, start with vanilla wafers; spread layer of goop, then nuts.
Keep making layers.
Top with Dream Whip, ground nuts and cherries.
Add 2 teaspoons sugar to Dream Whip.
Make this a day ahead.
Keeps well.

title: cheese mold
directions: Put in food processor and blend until creamy.
Pour into greased salad ring mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold onto dish.
Fill center with strawberry preserves.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken with brown rice and carrots
directions: Add rice to a large saucepan of salted water; boil for 15 minutes and drain.
In a small saucepan, bring 1/3 cup of water to a boil.
Add the rice and cook, covered, for 15 minutes more or until it's tender and liquid is absorbed.
Keep the rice covered until ready to use.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve sugar, yeast and salt in water.
Add flour and mix, then knead good.
Let rise at least 1 hour.
Store leftovers in icebox and is better the next day.
Bake at 450°.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: double layer chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix all ingredients together and cook at 325° until cake springs back with touch of hand.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Fry out hamburger meat in a deep pot and drain off fat.
Add the Veg-All, tomatoes, peeled and diced potatoes and the water. Let cook for about 3 hours.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix coconut and pecans and pour in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix cake mix by directions on package and pour over coconut and pecans.
Blend cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: curried turkey salad
directions: Cook turkey breast overnight on high in crock-pot.
Cool, remove from bone and cube, approximately 1/4 to 1/8-inch size. Add and mix the 4 other ingredients.
Keep refrigerated until serving.

title: venison steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except venison steak in a large bowl. Tenderize venison steak and place on foil in a shallow baking dish.
Pour mixture over steak and seal foil.
Bake for 2 hours in a preheated 350° oven.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese with onion soup.
Cut crusts off bread and flatten with rolling pin, then keep moist under a damp towel. Spread bread slice with cream cheese mixture.
Place asparagus spear at one end and roll up.
Cut into three pieces and place, seam side down, on cookie sheet.
Melt butter and add onion powder, parsley and paprika.
Brush this mixture over tops of rolls.
Bake at 400°
for 10 to 15 minutes, until slightly brown.

title: pear preserves
directions: Combine sugar and water in a large Dutch oven. Bring mixture to a boil, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves. Cook at a rolling boil 5 minutes. Add pears and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until pears are transparent.

title: grilled corn with lime butter
directions: You will need some kitchen twine or unwaxed dental floss for this recipe.

title: curried pork with rice
directions: Bake pork until done.
Chop apples and onions and saute in oil until tender.
Stir in flour, salt, ginger and curry powder.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened and pour over pork.
Serve over brown rice.

title: evelyn's caramel corn
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add soda and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Pour over popped corn in large bowl.
Place on 2 jelly roll pans (15 x 10 x 1-inch) or 1 large roasting pan.
Bake at 200° for an hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
When cool, place in covered container.

title: spiced peaches
directions: In a large saucepan, bring the first 4 ingredients to the boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add peaches; simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until

heated through. Place into a shallow baking dish. Cover and chill for 8 hours. Drain. Discard cloves. Spoon into serving dishes. Garnish with a dollop of sour cream and a sprinkle of brown sugar. Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly frosted salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1/2 cup juice and set aside.
Combine gelatin in a large mixing bowl.
Add 2 cups boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Add bananas, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Combine flour and sugar in a medium saucepan, mixing well.
Stir in egg and reserved pineapple juice; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Cool. Prepare whipped topping mix according to package.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Fold in cooked mixture; spread over gelatin mixture.
Chill.
Makes 15 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Slice the squash into bite-size pieces. Place the pieces in a 2-quart microwave-safe casserole and add the water. Cover and microwave on High for 3 minutes. Add the sauerkraut, caraway seeds, mustard and meat, mixing well. Cover and microwave on High for 6 minutes, stirring halfway through. Stir in the cheese and microwave for 3 to 5 more minutes or until the cheese is melted. Yield: 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, cream cheese and margarine.
Mix at medium speed until well blended.
Blend in bananas and eggs.
Add combined remaining ingredients, mixing until just moistened.
Fold in nuts. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: shrimp supreme
directions: Combine shrimp soup and celery soup in double boiler; stir until soft and soupy.
Add sherry, Tabasco and shrimp and cook until bubbly.
Serve over yellow rice.
(Follow directions on package.)
Have side dish of chutney.

title: reunion baked beans
directions: Mix
all together and bake at 350° until it bubbles all over top.

title: layered lemon dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour with a pastry blender until it resembles coarse meal.
Stir 1/2 cup of pecans into flour mixture.
Press pecan mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown; cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas; mix.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in center.

title: deer b~b~q
directions: In a crock pot layer onions then deer meat sliced one inch thick.
On each layer add hot sauce, Mrs. Dash, salt, and pepper. Continue to layer to the top of the crock pot.
On the top layer pour the Worcestershire sauce over meat then add lemon slices as top layer.
Cook meat until it falls apart, drain off liquid, crumble meat and add BBQ sauce.

title: dried apple and molasses stack cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Then add milk and dry ingredients.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Make the layers real thin.
It makes 5 to 6 thin layers.
Bake at 350°.
Have dried apples cooked and mashed up very fine.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg to apples.
Then put cooked dried apples between each layer.

title: sands dabs
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add remaining ingredients. Pinch off bits of dough and roll.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Should not let them brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: "ham-in-the-can"
directions: Punch 4 holes in the ham can. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain and pour sauce through holes.
Bake 1 hour longer.

title: potato souffle
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Peel and mash until lumps disappear.
Add all ingredients, one at a time.
Mix until slightly firm.
Grease baking pan.
Add mixture and bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour, until golden brown.
Top with marshmallows.

title: iced tea
directions: Boil tea bags; pour water in quart jug.
Add sugar, lemon slices and water.
Stir and add ice cubes as desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine the apples with the orange juice, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Place in bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Combine the flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt and butter. Sprinkle over the apples. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal pumpkin bars
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add pumpkin, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in a greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: emerald isle cheesecake
directions: In bowl cream the cream cheese and combine with pudding and milk and stir until smooth.
Add mint, coloring and chocolate chips.
Pile into pie shell and chill.
Decorate top with shamrock or other designs.

title: biker cake
directions: Mix cherry filling and pineapple; put on bottom of ungreased oblong cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over the top.
Sprinkle melted butter over top of cake mix.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° until top is brown.
Serve at room temperature with Cool Whip.

title: crab mornay
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in medium saucepan and remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt and cayenne.
Gradually stir in milk and cream.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Add lemon juice and crab meat.
Pour over spinach. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and paprika.
Bake 15 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Serve over toast.
Serves 4 to 6 on buttered toast slices.

title: smoked chicken and rosemary linguini
directions: Saute olive oil, garlic and chicken cubes.
Deglaze with wine and reduce.
Add cream and rosemary, boil.
Add cooked pasta. Stir constantly until sauce is thick and clinging to noodles.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix together in bowl the Jell-O, boiling water and the cream cheese.
Then add mayonnaise, mix.
Add cold water, pineapple and chopped pecans.
Put in flat, long bowl (10 x 14-inch) and refrigerate until set.

title: cherry crumble
directions: Spread pie filling in 9 x 11-inch cake pan.
Cut butter into dry cake mix, until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over cherries. Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ben's chocolate cake surprise
directions: Mix together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Cream together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in sauerkraut.

title: open line aloha bread
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the mashed bananas.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir until mixed.
Add the pineapple and coconut. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Put in 9-inch graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: dill bean sticks
directions: Wash and clean beans. Leave whole. Parboil, covered, in unsalted boiling water about 10 minutes or until just crisply tender. Drain and rinse with cold water. Put half clove of garlic and head of one fresh dill in each jar. Pack beans in jars upright. Heat vinegar, salt and cayenne to boiling. Pour into jars and seal. Liquid will cover four 16 ounce jars.

title: frankfurter meat loaf
directions: Grind hot dogs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: receta compartida(shared recipe)
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add pimentos, pepper, mushrooms and onion.
Saute until tender.
In a casserole dish, place soup, rice, water and salt; mix well.
Add sauteed mixture; stir very well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Dip fish in egg.
Roll in cornmeal and flour mixture.
Add lemon pepper seasoning on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: husband's delight cake
directions: Mix; spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let it cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: tom's easy chili
directions: In large pot (8 to 10-quart), simmer ground meat until fully cooked.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for a minimum of 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onion until tender.
Drain and save 1 cup water.
Combine butter, flour, milk and vegetable water to make a thin sauce.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Serve warm.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs, anise and milk.
Then mix flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add dry ingredients to liquid ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
You can add confectioners sugar when cooled.

title: bread sticks
directions: Decrust bread.
Mix other ingredients to spreading consistency.
Spread onto bread and cut into thirds.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Beat
cream
cheese,
sugar, eggs and vanilla together. Place vanilla wafers in cupcake liners and fill 2/3 full with mixture. Bake
at
375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until surface becomes dry and light brown.
Cool and top with any flavor pie filling
or serve plain.
Can be frozen if not topped with pie filling.

title: forever ambers
directions: Cut orange slice candy into small pieces.
Mix first three ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheet and cook at 250° for 30 minutes.
When cool, roll into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Mixture will be gooey.

title: macaroni-beef skillet supper
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Saute ground beef, onion and garlic in oil until meat loses its pink color and onions are tender.
Add pepper and remaining ingredients except macaroni.
Bring mixture to a boil, then simmer gently for about 5 minutes.
Mix in cooked macaroni and simmer for 5 more minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Empty bean dip on large platter.
Smooth.
Cream sour cream, 1/2 cup mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Stir in taco seasoning.
Put on top of bean mixture.
Thaw avocado dip.
Stir in 1/2 cup mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic and Tabasco.
Layer on top of cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle the lettuce, then the tomatoes, the green onions, then the cheese on top.

title: holiday walnut pie
directions: Combine first
4 ingredients.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in evaporated milk, corn syrup, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: cilla's blueberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease and flour an 8-inch square pan. Mix all ingredients in the order given except blueberries.
When ingredients have been mixed thoroughly, add blueberries.
Bake for 40 to 60 minutes, as needed.
Cool and slice.
Serve covered with a generous helping of lemon sauce.

title: scandanavian relish or salad
directions: Drain canned vegetables and add celery, green pepper, pimento and onion.
Mix together with wine vinegar, oil, sugar and salt and pepper.
Keeps forever.

title: cucumber icicle pickles(small cucumbers)
directions: Cut cucumbers lengthwise.
Boil pickling salt and water.
Pour over cucumbers; let stand 1 week, stirring each day.
Drain.
Pour boiling water over cucumbers for 1 day; drain.
Dissolve a lump of alum the size of a walnut in hot water and pour over cucumbers. Let stand for 1 day.
Drain.
Make a syrup of sugar and vinegar. Add small handful of mixed spices.
Bring to boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Next morning, drain and rinse.
Bring syrup to boil. Pour over cucumbers.
Do this 2 more mornings.
On 4th morning, pack cucumbers in hot, sterilized jars.
Bring syrup to boil; pour over cucumbers and seal jars.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute butter, steak sauce, salt, pepper, paprika, mushrooms and cheese.
Add liquid from peas.
Cook until cheese melts.
Put peas in bottom of casserole.
Add beans.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with croutons before serving and after finished baking.

title: cindy's snickerdoodles
directions: Beat butter and sugar thoroughly in a large mixing bowl of electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time, then add flavorings and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to other mixture, then by hand, stir in grated orange rind.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoons into bowl of granulated sugar. Roll into balls and place 1 1/2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 14 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes about 7 dozen cookies.
Freezes well. (Cookies will rise as they bake, then fall.
For a crisp cookie, bake until falling occurs.)

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Cream oil, eggs and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and blend together well. Pour into prepared tube pan. Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes. Add topping when cake is cool.

title: evie's coffee cake
directions: *Put 2 teaspoons of vinegar in sweet milk to make it sour milk.

title: crock-pot mushroom stew
directions: Wash and slice potatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Place in slow cooker. Add remaining ingredients, plus about 1/2 cup water.
Cook on low heat 8 to 10 hours.

title: peanut butter-chocolate squares
directions: Mix peanut butter with melted margarine.
Add powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well (use a spoon) and pat in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Melt or microwave chocolate with 1 to 2 tablespoons margarine.
Spread on top.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours and cut in squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mushroom meat puffs
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the soup and form into balls which are not too compact.
Sprinkle with flour and brown well in hot fat.
Over these, pour the can of soup diluted with 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh blueberry crunch
directions: Place blueberries in a 2-quart baking dish, spreading evenly. Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pineapple air cake
directions: Divide angel food cake with serrated knife into 3 layers.
Mix Cool Whip with well drained pineapple.
Frost each layer and top and sides of cake with this mixture.
This is easy and very lite for low-fat diets.

title: fresh fruit crisp
directions: Combine oats, brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Set aside.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
When cool crumble into small pieces.
In a large punch bowl or large glass bowl start with cake on bottom.
Layer with pudding, cherry pie filling, pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat.
Then end with Cool Whip and nuts on top.

title: hawaiian chicken salad
directions: Stew chicken and cut into chunks. Allow cream cheese to reach room temperature or microwave until soft. Mix all of the ingredients together and season to taste with the salt, pepper and onion salt.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 13 x 9-inch greased ovenproof pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: italian sausage and peppershouston, texas
directions: Puncture sausage and simmer in 1/4 c. water in a fairly deep fry pan for about 15 minutes or until all color has changed. Uncover and raise heat to evaporate water.
Brown the sausage and slice into 2 lengths.
Stir in onion, peppers, garlic, basil and spaghetti sauce.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes. While cooking, boil and drain pasta (uses a stockpot).
Toss together.

title: pig pickin
directions: Mix well and bake as box indicates for greased pan size.

title: pears in caramel sauce(serves 6)
directions: Peel and split pears.
Remove seeds and core.
Place flat side down in a baking dish in a single layer.

title: lizzies
directions: Mix raisins and bourbon well; let stand 1 hour.
Sift together the flour and spices; set aside.
Place butter in a large mixing bowl.
Add brown sugar and eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy. Beat in flour mixture.
Stir in raisins, pecans, pineapple and cherries.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for about 15 minutes or until firm.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Can be frozen.

title: california potatoes
directions: Grate potatoes.
Mix soup, sour cream, melted oleo, onions and cheese; add to potatoes.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger and onion.
Cook spaghetti until done and drain well.
Mix egg and milk and pour over spaghetti.
Mix well.
Add sauce, hamburger and green pepper and mix.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange pepperoni slices on top and spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not cover; let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. In large bowl beat sugar, margarine, egg whites and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients alternately with water. Stir in morsels.
Spread into greased 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: chocolate pecan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 inch square baking pan.
In a small bowl, mix together, flour and baking soda.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Bring to boil over medium heat and remove immediately.
Stir in 1 cup of the chocolate morsels and vanilla until chocolate is melted and mixture is smooth.
Transfer mixture to a medium bowl.
Cool completely.
Stir in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually stir in flour mixture until smooth.
Stir in remaining chocolate morsels and nuts into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Drain spaghetti; chop chicken and combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; top with crumbled Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake on 350° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla; mix until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture and stir in chips and nuts. (Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan. Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Pour into serving bowls.
Serve warm or cold sprinkled with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add rice and raisins to milk and pudding mixture before cooking.
Serves 10.

title: chicken almondine
directions: Saute almonds in butter until brown (about 4 minutes).
Remove almonds.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and dust chicken.
Brown chicken in pan with butter.
After brown, stir in wine.
Cover and cook on low heat for 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken. Add almonds to sauce.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.

title: creamy pesto dip
directions: Mix sour cream and pesto until well blended. Sprinkle with chopped tomato. Serve with vegetables. This has 2 grams carbohydrate.

title: ravioli vegetable casserole
directions: Trim and slice eggplant and zucchini.
Combine flour and salt. Coat eggplant and zucchini with seasoned flour; fry in hot oil until tender and slightly browned, adding oil if necessary.
Place vegetables in the bottom of a casserole.
Saute onion in remaining oil.
Top eggplant and zucchini with onion and beef ravioli. Sprinkle cheese over casserole.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Blend sugar and flour; add 6 tablespoons pineapple juice.
Mix well; add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Toss and place in buttered oblong baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Pour melted butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be used as side dish or dessert.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze. When you get ready for it, just take it out of the freezer and into punch bowl. Mix up 2 liters of 7-Up or Sprite into it. You can use diet if you want.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Combine chicken, salsa, onion and cumin.
Mix well.
Heat about 1/2-inch oil in small skillet until hot, but not smoking. Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 2 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels. Spoon 1 tablespoon chicken mixture and 1 tablespoon cheese down center of each tortilla. Roll tightly and secure with wooden pick.
Place, seam side down, on baking sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 400° about 18 to 20 minutes or until crisp. Serve warm with guacamole and additional salsa.
Makes 32.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms without stems in an ovenproof baking dish under the broiler for 3 minutes.

title: chicken livers saute
directions: Clean and cut livers into halves.
Saute in butter in frypan over low heat until lightly browned. Remove livers.
Add flour; stir. Add water. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add salt and livers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Serve over cooked rice.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Spread pie filling in oblong cake pan.	Sprinkle yellow cake mix
on top.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350°
until hot and bubbly.
Serve hot with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: sesame vegetables and rice
directions: Saute vegetables in sesame oil.
Add oyster sauce, cilantro and vegetables.
Warm and season to taste.

title: fruit crisp
directions: Put fruit in casserole dish.
Mix Bisquick, egg and sugar until coarse.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Melt 1 stick margarine and sprinkle over mixture; bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: sue's chicken pie
directions: Shred or finely cut leftover cooked chicken.
Mix soup and milk and add to chicken.
Partially cook vegetables; drain and stir into chicken mixture.
Bake biscuits.
Pour chicken mixture into a casserole dish and place biscuits on top.
Put casserole back in the oven to heat through.

title: typical italian salad
directions: Rub garlic over sides of salad bowl.
Mix together oil, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Place greens in salad bowl and pour dressing over them.
Mix very well.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour in rectangular size pan.
Then, sprinkle over the top 1/2 cup of brown sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pig stomach
directions: Mix onion, celery, potatoes, parsley, pepper, salt and cut smoked sausage.
Stuff pig stomach with mixture and close with cooking clips.
Place stuffed stomach in a roasting pan with 1/2 cup water and bake, covered, at 350°
for 2 hours.
Uncover and bake another hour or until skin is brown and tender.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch square pan (or 9 to 10-inch casserole dish).
Mix pineapple, melted butter and brown sugar together and spread in bottom of pan.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
With an electric mixer, cream the sugar and butter.
Add the egg, milk and vanilla extract and blend.
Add dry ingredients, stir to moisten, then beat for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour over fruit mixture and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn cake upside-down onto serving plate immediately after taking out of oven.
Leave pan over cake for 5 minutes and then remove.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, to 234°, or until a few drops of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; cool at room temperature, without stirring, until lukewarm, 135°.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until creamy and quite stiff.
Shape with fingers into small pieces to resemble potatoes.
Roll in 2 teaspoons cinnamon.

title: chicken with mushroom gravy
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown chicken real well.
Put the mushroom soup in pot.
Add 1 soup can of milk.
Put chicken in gravy and cook for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender and well done.
Great with mashed potatoes.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in large bowl; stir in flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and mix well.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar; cut into bars.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut celery and egg into small, even pieces.
Add ingredients to cooked salad dressing or dressing of your choice.
Serve cold.

title: terri's vegetable pizza
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix. Bake rolls, which have been spread on a cookie sheet and pinched to stay together, according to directions.
Spread cream cheese mixture on rolls.
Top with broccoli, onions, green peppers, black or green olives, cauliflower, tomatoes and mushrooms.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook onion and celery in small amount of chicken broth until tender.

Layer in microwave casserole dish: taco shells (broken in pieces), chicken, mushrooms, onion, celery and a layer of cheese. Mix the soups and tomatoes together and add garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake on High for about 20 minutes in microwave.

title: chicken and sour cream
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken breast in mixture.
Marinate overnight.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Combine mashed banana, sour milk and vanilla.
Mix the dry ingredients alternately with the wet into the creamed mixture.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: richie rich chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream softened butter with sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix in medium bowl the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger. Add to butter mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Scoop large ball with spoon and roll dough in confectioners sugar.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet for 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes approximately 24 cookies.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake white cake according to package directions in 13 x 9-inch pan.
While cake is baking, add water to Jell-O, stirring to dissolve Jell-O.
Pierce entire top of hot cake with small holes, piercing through to bottom of cake (a large meat fork works well). Slowly drizzle Jell-O into holes, covering entire cake. Refrigerate until cold.
Spread pie filling over top of cake. Spread Cool Whip over pie filling.
Garnish with fresh berries, if desired.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt caramel and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine remaining milk, butter and cake mix.
Mix well. Press half of the mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 6 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips and 1 cup walnuts over baked crust.
Top with caramel mixture, spreading to edge. Drop remaining cake mixture on top of caramel; press evenly.
Top with remaining walnuts.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: low calorie blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease muffin pan or use foil or paper baking cups.
Thoroughly mix flours, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg with fork or whisk, in a small bowl. Whisk in milk and butter.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Add blueberries and lemon peel.
Fold in with rubber spatula just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Scoop batter into muffin cups.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Serve hot or warm.

title: hot winter juices
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat (do not boil).
Very festive for cold days.

title: busy woman's stew
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Add beans, Ro-Tel tomatoes and soup.
Simmer 30 minutes or longer.

title: jello pretzel pie
directions: Mix together and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then let cool.

title: croutons
directions: Dice bread.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with Lawry's, onion and garlic salts.
Toast in very slow oven.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix beaten eggs and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Add fruit cocktail.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine the blackberries, 1 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon extract. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Partially thaw ice cream.
Put into pie crust.
Drizzle some chocolate syrup and let freeze.
Spread thawed Cool Whip on top. Return to freezer.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits.
Sprinkle pudding on.
Let stand 5 minutes. Blend.
Yields about 6 1/2 cups.

title: english toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Butter 13 x 9-inch pan. Arrange saltines, right side up, in a single layer to cover pan.
Melt butter and sugar over medium heat; bring to a boil.

Boil for 3 minutes, stirring often. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Pour over saltines and spread evenly. Bake 5 minutes. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Sprinkle chips over and spread as they melt. Sprinkle on pecans; cut into squares.

title: devon apple cake
directions: Put oil, sugar and beaten eggs into a bowl.
Sift together flour, spices and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Add vanilla and apples last.
Turn into a greased angel food pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Dust with confectioners sugar just before serving.

title: split seconds
directions: In a large bowl, beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg; beat well.
Next, stir in flour and baking powder.
Blend well.
On lightly floured surface, divide dough into 4 equal parts.
Shape each into a roll, 12 x 3/4-inches.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using handle of wooden spoon or finger, make a depression lengthwise down center of each roll, about 1/2-inch wide and 1/4-inch deep.
Fill each depression with preserves.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool slightly and cut diagonally into bars.

title: beef tips and gravy
directions: Place onion rings in baking dish.
Cover with beef tips.
Mix soups and pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 250° for 3 hours. Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Place ingredients in glass jar with screw-type lid.
Shake until well blended.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Combine all ingredients except pectin and boil for 6 minutes. Stir in pectin and boil 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; skim off foam with metal spoon.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together and put into graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.

title: hungarian kifliks
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in bowl until consistency of medium dough.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Chill for 3 hours.
Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff.
Fold in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, cinnamon and walnuts.
Roll each dough ball into a circle on floured surface. Cut into wedges; spread with walnut mixture.
Roll up from wide end.
Shape into crescents on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese, then beat it with mixer.
Add Cheddar cheese, then the next 8 ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Chill for several hours.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in pecans and/or paprika.

title: french onion soup for two
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions and flour and continue to cook.
Stir in broth and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Divide soup into bowls.
Top each bowl with 2 slices of bread and sprinkle with cheeses.
Brown slightly under broiler.

title: le negre(flourless chocolate cake from the aquitaine coast of france)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter an 8-inch round cake pan.
Break chocolate up and heat to melt over hot water.
Add 7 ounces butter to chocolate and stir with spatula until smooth.
Add 1/2 the sugar to egg yolks and whisk until the mixture is pale in color. Beat into the chocolate.
Beat egg whites into soft peaks. Gradually add the remaining sugar, beating until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Fold gently into chocolate with spatula.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 40 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Let cake rest at room temperature for 10 minutes before turning out of pan.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: hot salt pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in cold water.
Drain.
Put a grape leaf in bottom of each jar, then pack cucumbers in jars as tight as possible.
Add alum, dill seed, red pepper and garlic cloves. Bring vinegar, water and salt to boil.
Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: dump cake
directions: *You may substitute any flavor, such as blueberry, raspberry, etc.

title: fish and veggies in cooking bag(quick and easy dinner, less than 1 hour)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in cooking bag to coat. Place in baking dish.
Sprinkle fish with seasoning and cheese. Roll each fillet, starting at narrow end.
Place fish rolls, seam side down, in center of bag, forming 2 rows.
Lay veggies around fish rolls.
Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Close bag; make half-inch slits in top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13 inch pan 1 roll of crescent rolls.
With mixer, beat cream cheese till light and fluffy.
Then add egg yolk, sugar and vanilla, Mix well.
Pour on top of crescent rolls in pan. Layer second roll on top of mixture.
Whip egg white slightly, them spread on top of rolls.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake 350° oven for 30 minutes or till brown on top.
Cool.
Cut in slices, store in refrigerator.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into an 8 inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(If using pecans, cook a little longer.)
Take out and allow to cool before cutting.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight on kitchen counter.
Turn out onto floured board and knead lightly.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into rolls.
Place rolls on greased cookie sheet and let rise 4 to 6 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked ham
directions: Place ham, cut side down, on a rack or bed of crumbled foil in large pan.
Do not cover.
Place in a 325° oven and bake according to the following guide.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
I like it hot, so I use the Monterey Jack with jalapenos.

title: dill pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers overnight in cold water in crock.
Pack in jars and add dill, garlic, pepper and alum to each jar.
Cover with grape leaves.
Boil vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers and seal tight.
Set in cool place.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut up beef into strips or cubes and brown in cooking oil along with onions, garlic, salt and pepper. Add beef bouillon water and simmer 10 minutes. Add pepper slices and simmer another 5 to 10 minutes. Add tomatoes (undrained) and simmer 5 more minutes. Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water, along with soy sauce. Add to other ingredients to thicken.

title: quick peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix three ingredients (that is right, no flour) together with wooden spoon.
Roll the dough into small balls and press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes two dozen 1-inch cookies.

title: cooked potato salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add milk, mustard and vinegar.
In microwave-safe bowl, bring to boil.
Add butter.
Cook on High 3 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds to 1 minute or longer, until a thick, creamy consistency.
Pour over potato salad and cool.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon in large bowl.
Place in pan the butter, cocoa, water and oil.
Bring to a boil; pour on flour mixture while still hot.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Bake in a long greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail.
Add enough water to make 5 cups of liquid.
Heat 3 1/2 cups of liquid to boiling.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in the liquid.
Chill and add half of the fruit cocktail.
Congeal.
Cream the cheese until it is soft.
Heat 1 1/2 cups of liquid to boiling.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in it and chill.
Blend this mixture slowly with the cream cheese.
Add nuts.
Pour on top of first congealed mixture and put in refrigerator until entire mixture is congealed.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all together and put in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, then turn to 375° for 25 minutes more.

title: hillbilly pie
directions: No bowl needed.
Mix in baking pan.
Mix flour, sugar and baking powder; work soft oleo or butter into dry mixture with a fork.
Add milk; stir until mixture is moist and creamy.
Add fruit or pie filling.
Blend through batter with knife.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: nettie robinson's baked corn
directions: Mix cornstarch with the 3 tablespoons of milk.
Add salt.
Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Bake 3/4 hour at 375°.

title: baked broccoli with cheese and tomatoes
directions: Brown cut up garlic with oil to light brown.
Put in broccoli. Add 1/2 cup water in pot and cook, covered, 6 to 8 minutes.
Add Italian cheese.
Mix. Take out of pot.
Place in appropriate size baking pan.
Mix with macaroni.
You can add a few slices of cheese.
Even out and place sliced cheese on top of tomatoes.
Bake at 350° approximately 1/2 hour.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: fresh apple cake (layer)
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each.
Add apples and mix.
Add nuts and mix.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Add vanilla.
Bake in four layers at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Fresh Apple Cake Frosting.

title: shrimp ball(club member: terah smith)
directions: Chill drained shrimp; crush with fork. Add other ingredients. Form into ball. Serve with crackers.
